159typedef enum BusFocus {
160 BUS_FULL, /* The full bus indicated via --system or --user */
161 BUS_MANAGER, /* The manager itself, possibly directly, possibly via the bus */
162 _BUS_FOCUS_MAX
163} BusFocus;
164
165static sd_bus *busses[_BUS_FOCUS_MAX] = {};
166
167static int acquire_bus(BusFocus focus, sd_bus **ret) {
168 int r;
169
170 assert(focus < _BUS_FOCUS_MAX)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(focus < _BUS_FOCUS_MAX)),0
))) log_assert_failed("focus < _BUS_FOCUS_MAX", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 170, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); } while (0);
171 assert(ret)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(ret)),0))) log_assert_failed(
"ret", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 171, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__)
; } while (0);
172
173 /* We only go directly to the manager, if we are using a local transport */
174 if (arg_transport != BUS_TRANSPORT_LOCAL)
175 focus = BUS_FULL;
176
177 if (!busses[focus]) {
178 bool_Bool user;
179
180 user = arg_scope != UNIT_FILE_SYSTEM;
181
182 if (focus == BUS_MANAGER)
183 r = bus_connect_transport_systemd(arg_transport, arg_host, user, &busses[focus]);
184 else
185 r = bus_connect_transport(arg_transport, arg_host, user, &busses[focus]);
186 if (r < 0)
187 return log_error_errno(r, "Failed to connect to bus: %m")({ int _level = (3), _e = (r); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 187, __func__, "Failed to connect to bus: %m") : -abs(_e); }
);
188
189 (void) sd_bus_set_allow_interactive_authorization(busses[focus], arg_ask_password);
190 }
191
192 *ret = busses[focus];
193 return 0;
194}
195
196static void release_busses(void) {
197 BusFocus w;
198
199 for (w = 0; w < _BUS_FOCUS_MAX; w++)
200 busses[w] = sd_bus_flush_close_unref(busses[w]);
201}

203static void ask_password_agent_open_if_enabled(void) {
204
205 /* Open the password agent as a child process if necessary */
206
207 if (!arg_ask_password)
208 return;
209
210 if (arg_scope != UNIT_FILE_SYSTEM)
211 return;
212
213 if (arg_transport != BUS_TRANSPORT_LOCAL)
214 return;
215
216 ask_password_agent_open();
217}

235static OutputFlags get_output_flags(void) {
236 return
237 arg_all * OUTPUT_SHOW_ALL |
238 arg_full * OUTPUT_FULL_WIDTH |
239 (!on_tty() || pager_have()) * OUTPUT_FULL_WIDTH |
240 colors_enabled() * OUTPUT_COLOR |

244static int translate_bus_error_to_exit_status(int r, const sd_bus_error *error) {
245 assert(error)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(error)),0))) log_assert_failed
("error", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 245, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
246
247 if (!sd_bus_error_is_set(error))
248 return r;
249
250 if (sd_bus_error_has_name(error, SD_BUS_ERROR_ACCESS_DENIED"org.freedesktop.DBus.Error.AccessDenied") ||
251 sd_bus_error_has_name(error, BUS_ERROR_ONLY_BY_DEPENDENCY"org.freedesktop.systemd1.OnlyByDependency") ||
252 sd_bus_error_has_name(error, BUS_ERROR_NO_ISOLATION"org.freedesktop.systemd1.NoIsolation") ||
253 sd_bus_error_has_name(error, BUS_ERROR_TRANSACTION_IS_DESTRUCTIVE"org.freedesktop.systemd1.TransactionIsDestructive"))
254 return EXIT_NOPERMISSION;
255
256 if (sd_bus_error_has_name(error, BUS_ERROR_NO_SUCH_UNIT"org.freedesktop.systemd1.NoSuchUnit"))
257 return EXIT_NOTINSTALLED;
258
259 if (sd_bus_error_has_name(error, BUS_ERROR_JOB_TYPE_NOT_APPLICABLE"org.freedesktop.systemd1.JobTypeNotApplicable") ||
260 sd_bus_error_has_name(error, SD_BUS_ERROR_NOT_SUPPORTED"org.freedesktop.DBus.Error.NotSupported"))
261 return EXIT_NOTIMPLEMENTED;
262
263 if (sd_bus_error_has_name(error, BUS_ERROR_LOAD_FAILED"org.freedesktop.systemd1.LoadFailed"))
264 return EXIT_NOTCONFIGURED;
265
266 if (r != 0)
267 return r;
268
269 return EXIT_FAILURE1;
270}

272static bool_Bool install_client_side(void) {
273
274 /* Decides when to execute enable/disable/... operations
275 * client-side rather than server-side. */
276
277 if (running_in_chroot() > 0)
278 return true1;
279
280 if (sd_booted() <= 0)
281 return true1;
282
283 if (!isempty(arg_root))
284 return true1;
285
286 if (arg_scope == UNIT_FILE_GLOBAL)
287 return true1;
288
289 /* Unsupported environment variable, mostly for debugging purposes */
290 if (getenv_bool("SYSTEMCTL_INSTALL_CLIENT_SIDE") > 0)
291 return true1;
292
293 return false0;
294}

296static int compare_unit_info(const void *a, const void *b) {
297 const UnitInfo *u = a, *v = b;
298 const char *d1, *d2;
299 int r;
300
301 /* First, order by machine */
302 if (!u->machine && v->machine)
303 return -1;
304 if (u->machine && !v->machine)
305 return 1;
306 if (u->machine && v->machine) {
307 r = strcasecmp(u->machine, v->machine);
308 if (r != 0)
309 return r;
310 }
311
312 /* Second, order by unit type */
313 d1 = strrchr(u->id, '.');
314 d2 = strrchr(v->id, '.');
315 if (d1 && d2) {
316 r = strcasecmp(d1, d2);
317 if (r != 0)
318 return r;
319 }
320
321 /* Third, order by name */
322 return strcasecmp(u->id, v->id);
323}

325static bool_Bool output_show_unit(const UnitInfo *u, char **patterns) {
326 if (!strv_fnmatch_or_empty(patterns, u->id, FNM_NOESCAPE(1 << 1)))
327 return false0;
328
329 if (arg_types) {
330 const char *dot;
331
332 dot = strrchr(u->id, '.');
333 if (!dot)
334 return false0;
335
336 if (!strv_find(arg_types, dot+1))
337 return false0;
338 }
339
340 if (arg_all)
341 return true1;
342
343 if (u->job_id > 0)
344 return true1;
345
346 if (streq(u->active_state, "inactive")(strcmp((u->active_state),("inactive")) == 0) || u->following[0])
347 return false0;
348
349 return true1;
350}

515static int get_unit_list(

563 if (!GREEDY_REALLOC(*unit_infos, size, c+1)greedy_realloc((void**) &(*unit_infos), &(size), (c+1
), sizeof((*unit_infos)[0])))
564 return log_oom()log_oom_internal("src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 564, __func__);
565
566 (*unit_infos)[c++] = u;
567 }
568 if (r < 0)
569 return bus_log_parse_error(r);
570
571 r = sd_bus_message_exit_container(reply);
572 if (r < 0)
573 return bus_log_parse_error(r);
574
575 *_reply = reply;
576 reply = NULL((void*)0);
577
578 return c;
579}
580
581static void message_set_freep(Set **set) {
582 sd_bus_message *m;
583
584 while ((m = set_steal_first(*set)))
585 sd_bus_message_unref(m);
586
587 set_free(*set);
588}

590static int get_unit_list_recursive(
591 sd_bus *bus,
592 char **patterns,
593 UnitInfo **_unit_infos,
594 Set **_replies,
595 char ***_machines) {
596
597 _cleanup_free___attribute__((cleanup(freep))) UnitInfo *unit_infos = NULL((void*)0);
598 _cleanup_(message_set_freep)__attribute__((cleanup(message_set_freep))) Set *replies;
599 sd_bus_message *reply;
600 int c, r;
601
602 assert(bus)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(bus)),0))) log_assert_failed(

; } while (0);

); } while (0);

("_machines", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 605, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);

617 sd_bus_message_unref(reply);

619 }
620

622 _cleanup_strv_free___attribute__((cleanup(strv_freep))) char **machines = NULL((void*)0);

, 627, __func__, "Failed to get machine names: %m") : -abs(_e
); });
628
629 STRV_FOREACH(i, machines)for ((i) = (machines); (i) && *(i); (i)++) {

637 }
638

640 if (k < 0)

643 c = k;
644
645 r = set_put(replies, reply);
646 if (r < 0) {
647 sd_bus_message_unref(reply);
648 return log_oom()log_oom_internal("src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 648, __func__);
649 }
650 }
651
652 *_machines = machines;
653 machines = NULL((void*)0);
654 } else
655 *_machines = NULL((void*)0);
656

658 unit_infos = NULL((void*)0);
659

666static int list_units(int argc, char *argv[], void *userdata) {
667 _cleanup_free___attribute__((cleanup(freep))) UnitInfo *unit_infos = NULL((void*)0);
668 _cleanup_(message_set_freep)__attribute__((cleanup(message_set_freep))) Set *replies = NULL((void*)0);
669 _cleanup_strv_free___attribute__((cleanup(strv_freep))) char **machines = NULL((void*)0);
670 sd_bus *bus;
671 int r;
672
673 pager_open(arg_no_pager, false0);
674
675 r = acquire_bus(BUS_MANAGER, &bus);
676 if (r < 0)
677 return r;
678
679 r = get_unit_list_recursive(bus, strv_skip(argv, 1), &unit_infos, &replies, &machines);
680 if (r < 0)
681 return r;
682
683 qsort_safe(unit_infos, r, sizeof(UnitInfo), compare_unit_info);
684 return output_units_list(unit_infos, r);
685}

713static int get_listening(
714 sd_bus *bus,
715 const char* unit_path,
716 char*** listening) {
717
718 _cleanup_(sd_bus_error_free)__attribute__((cleanup(sd_bus_error_free))) sd_bus_error error = SD_BUS_ERROR_NULL((const sd_bus_error) {(((void*)0)), (((void*)0)), 0});
719 _cleanup_(sd_bus_message_unrefp)__attribute__((cleanup(sd_bus_message_unrefp))) sd_bus_message *reply = NULL((void*)0);
720 const char *type, *path;
721 int r, n = 0;
722
723 r = sd_bus_get_property(
724 bus,
725 "org.freedesktop.systemd1",
726 unit_path,
727 "org.freedesktop.systemd1.Socket",
728 "Listen",
729 &error,
730 &reply,
731 "a(ss)");
732 if (r < 0)
733 return log_error_errno(r, "Failed to get list of listening sockets: %s", bus_error_message(&error, r))({ int _level = (3), _e = (r); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 733, __func__, "Failed to get list of listening sockets: %s"
, bus_error_message(&error, r)) : -abs(_e); });
734
735 r = sd_bus_message_enter_container(reply, SD_BUS_TYPE_ARRAY, "(ss)");
736 if (r < 0)
737 return bus_log_parse_error(r);
738
739 while ((r = sd_bus_message_read(reply, "(ss)", &type, &path)) > 0) {
740
741 r = strv_extend(listening, type);
742 if (r < 0)
743 return log_oom()log_oom_internal("src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 743, __func__);
744
745 r = strv_extend(listening, path);
746 if (r < 0)
747 return log_oom()log_oom_internal("src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 747, __func__);
748
749 n++;
750 }
751 if (r < 0)
752 return bus_log_parse_error(r);
753
754 r = sd_bus_message_exit_container(reply);
755 if (r < 0)
756 return bus_log_parse_error(r);
757
758 return n;
759}

761struct socket_info {
762 const char *machine;
763 const char* id;
764
765 char* type;
766 char* path;
767
768 /* Note: triggered is a list here, although it almost certainly
769 * will always be one unit. Nevertheless, dbus API allows for multiple
770 * values, so let's follow that. */
771 char** triggered;
772
773 /* The strv above is shared. free is set only in the first one. */
774 bool_Bool own_triggered;
775};
776
777static int socket_info_compare(const struct socket_info *a, const struct socket_info *b) {
778 int o;
779
780 assert(a)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(a)),0))) log_assert_failed("a"
, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 780, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); } while
(0);
781 assert(b)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(b)),0))) log_assert_failed("b"
, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 781, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); } while
(0);
782
783 if (!a->machine && b->machine)
784 return -1;
785 if (a->machine && !b->machine)
786 return 1;
787 if (a->machine && b->machine) {
788 o = strcasecmp(a->machine, b->machine);
789 if (o != 0)
790 return o;
791 }
792
793 o = strcmp(a->path, b->path);
794 if (o == 0)
795 o = strcmp(a->type, b->type);
796
797 return o;
798}

873static int list_sockets(int argc, char *argv[], void *userdata) {
874 _cleanup_(message_set_freep)__attribute__((cleanup(message_set_freep))) Set *replies = NULL((void*)0);
875 _cleanup_strv_free___attribute__((cleanup(strv_freep))) char **machines = NULL((void*)0);
876 _cleanup_free___attribute__((cleanup(freep))) UnitInfo *unit_infos = NULL((void*)0);
877 _cleanup_free___attribute__((cleanup(freep))) struct socket_info *socket_infos = NULL((void*)0);
878 const UnitInfo *u;
879 struct socket_info *s;
880 unsigned cs = 0;
881 size_t size = 0;
882 int r = 0, n;
883 sd_bus *bus;
884
885 pager_open(arg_no_pager, false0);
886
887 r = acquire_bus(BUS_MANAGER, &bus);
888 if (r < 0)
889 return r;
890
891 n = get_unit_list_recursive(bus, strv_skip(argv, 1), &unit_infos, &replies, &machines);
892 if (n < 0)
893 return n;
894
895 for (u = unit_infos; u < unit_infos + n; u++) {
896 _cleanup_strv_free___attribute__((cleanup(strv_freep))) char **listening = NULL((void*)0), **triggered = NULL((void*)0);
897 int i, c;
898
899 if (!endswith(u->id, ".socket"))
900 continue;
901
902 r = get_triggered_units(bus, u->unit_path, &triggered);
903 if (r < 0)
904 goto cleanup;
905
906 c = get_listening(bus, u->unit_path, &listening);
907 if (c < 0) {
908 r = c;
909 goto cleanup;
910 }
911
912 if (!GREEDY_REALLOC(socket_infos, size, cs + c)greedy_realloc((void**) &(socket_infos), &(size), (cs
+ c), sizeof((socket_infos)[0]))) {
913 r = log_oom()log_oom_internal("src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 913, __func__);
914 goto cleanup;
915 }
916
917 for (i = 0; i < c; i++)
918 socket_infos[cs + i] = (struct socket_info) {
919 .machine = u->machine,
920 .id = u->id,
921 .type = listening[i*2],
922 .path = listening[i*2 + 1],
923 .triggered = triggered,
924 .own_triggered = i==0,
925 };
926
927 /* from this point on we will cleanup those socket_infos */
928 cs += c;
929 free(listening);
930 listening = triggered = NULL((void*)0); /* avoid cleanup */
931 }
932
933 qsort_safe(socket_infos, cs, sizeof(struct socket_info),
934 (__compar_fn_t) socket_info_compare);
935
936 output_sockets_list(socket_infos, cs);
937
938 cleanup:
939 assert(cs == 0 || socket_infos)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(cs == 0 || socket_infos)),0))
) log_assert_failed("cs == 0 || socket_infos", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 939, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); } while (0);
940 for (s = socket_infos; s < socket_infos + cs; s++) {
941 free(s->type);
942 free(s->path);
943 if (s->own_triggered)
944 strv_free(s->triggered);
945 }
946
947 return r;
948}

1018struct timer_info {
1019 const char* machine;
1020 const char* id;
1021 usec_t next_elapse;
1022 usec_t last_trigger;
1023 char** triggered;
1024};
1025
1026static int timer_info_compare(const struct timer_info *a, const struct timer_info *b) {
1027 int o;
1028
1029 assert(a)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(a)),0))) log_assert_failed("a"
, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 1029, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); } while
(0);
1030 assert(b)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(b)),0))) log_assert_failed("b"
, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 1030, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); } while
(0);
1031
1032 if (!a->machine && b->machine)
1033 return -1;
1034 if (a->machine && !b->machine)
1035 return 1;
1036 if (a->machine && b->machine) {
1037 o = strcasecmp(a->machine, b->machine);
1038 if (o != 0)
1039 return o;
1040 }
1041
1042 if (a->next_elapse < b->next_elapse)
1043 return -1;
1044 if (a->next_elapse > b->next_elapse)
1045 return 1;
1046
1047 return strcmp(a->id, b->id);
1048}
1049
1050static int output_timers_list(struct timer_info *timer_infos, unsigned n) {
1051 struct timer_info *t;
1052 unsigned
1053 nextlen = strlen("NEXT"),
1054 leftlen = strlen("LEFT"),
1055 lastlen = strlen("LAST"),
1056 passedlen = strlen("PASSED"),
1057 unitlen = strlen("UNIT"),
1058 activatelen = strlen("ACTIVATES");
1059

1061
1062 assert(timer_infos || n == 0)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(timer_infos || n == 0)),0))) log_assert_failed

); } while (0);
1063
1064 for (t = timer_infos; t < timer_infos + n; t++) {
1065 unsigned ul = 0;
1066 char **a;
1067
1068 if (t->next_elapse > 0) {
1069 char tstamp[FORMAT_TIMESTAMP_MAX((4*4+1)+11+9+4+1)] = "", trel[FORMAT_TIMESTAMP_RELATIVE_MAX256] = "";
1070
1071 format_timestamp(tstamp, sizeof(tstamp), t->next_elapse);

1154static usec_t calc_next_elapse(dual_timestamp *nw, dual_timestamp *next) {
1155 usec_t next_elapse;
1156
1157 assert(nw)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(nw)),0))) log_assert_failed("nw"
, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 1157, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); } while
(0);
1158 assert(next)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(next)),0))) log_assert_failed
("next", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 1158, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
1159
1160 if (next->monotonic != USEC_INFINITY((usec_t) -1) && next->monotonic > 0) {
1161 usec_t converted;
1162
1163 if (next->monotonic > nw->monotonic)
1164 converted = nw->realtime + (next->monotonic - nw->monotonic);
1165 else
1166 converted = nw->realtime - (nw->monotonic - next->monotonic);
1167
1168 if (next->realtime != USEC_INFINITY((usec_t) -1) && next->realtime > 0)
1169 next_elapse = MIN(converted, next->realtime)__extension__ ({ const typeof((converted)) __unique_prefix_A502
= ((converted)); const typeof((next->realtime)) __unique_prefix_B503
= ((next->realtime)); __unique_prefix_A502 < __unique_prefix_B503
? __unique_prefix_A502 : __unique_prefix_B503; });
1170 else
1171 next_elapse = converted;
1172
1173 } else
1174 next_elapse = next->realtime;
1175
1176 return next_elapse;
1177}

1179static int list_timers(int argc, char *argv[], void *userdata) {
1180 _cleanup_(message_set_freep)__attribute__((cleanup(message_set_freep))) Set *replies = NULL((void*)0);
1181 _cleanup_strv_free___attribute__((cleanup(strv_freep))) char **machines = NULL((void*)0);
1182 _cleanup_free___attribute__((cleanup(freep))) struct timer_info *timer_infos = NULL((void*)0);
1183 _cleanup_free___attribute__((cleanup(freep))) UnitInfo *unit_infos = NULL((void*)0);
1184 struct timer_info *t;
1185 const UnitInfo *u;
1186 size_t size = 0;
1187 int n, c = 0;
1188 dual_timestamp nw;
1189 sd_bus *bus;
1190 int r = 0;
1191
1192 pager_open(arg_no_pager, false0);
1193
1194 r = acquire_bus(BUS_MANAGER, &bus);
1195 if (r < 0)
1196 return r;
1197
1198 n = get_unit_list_recursive(bus, strv_skip(argv, 1), &unit_infos, &replies, &machines);
1199 if (n < 0)
1200 return n;
1201
1202 dual_timestamp_get(&nw);
1203
1204 for (u = unit_infos; u < unit_infos + n; u++) {
1205 _cleanup_strv_free___attribute__((cleanup(strv_freep))) char **triggered = NULL((void*)0);
1206 dual_timestamp next = DUAL_TIMESTAMP_NULL((struct dual_timestamp) { 0ULL, 0ULL });
1207 usec_t m, last = 0;
1208
1209 if (!endswith(u->id, ".timer"))
1210 continue;
1211
1212 r = get_triggered_units(bus, u->unit_path, &triggered);
1213 if (r < 0)
1214 goto cleanup;
1215
1216 r = get_next_elapse(bus, u->unit_path, &next);
1217 if (r < 0)
1218 goto cleanup;
1219
1220 get_last_trigger(bus, u->unit_path, &last);
1221
1222 if (!GREEDY_REALLOC(timer_infos, size, c+1)greedy_realloc((void**) &(timer_infos), &(size), (c+1
), sizeof((timer_infos)[0]))) {
1223 r = log_oom()log_oom_internal("src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 1223, __func__);
1224 goto cleanup;
1225 }
1226
1227 m = calc_next_elapse(&nw, &next);
1228
1229 timer_infos[c++] = (struct timer_info) {
1230 .machine = u->machine,
1231 .id = u->id,
1232 .next_elapse = m,
1233 .last_trigger = last,
1234 .triggered = triggered,
1235 };
1236
1237 triggered = NULL((void*)0); /* avoid cleanup */
1238 }
1239
1240 qsort_safe(timer_infos, c, sizeof(struct timer_info),
1241 (__compar_fn_t) timer_info_compare);
1242
1243 output_timers_list(timer_infos, c);
1244
1245 cleanup:
1246 for (t = timer_infos; t < timer_infos + c; t++)
1247 strv_free(t->triggered);
1248
1249 return r;
1250}
1251
1252static int compare_unit_file_list(const void *a, const void *b) {
1253 const char *d1, *d2;
1254 const UnitFileList *u = a, *v = b;
1255
1256 d1 = strrchr(u->path, '.');
1257 d2 = strrchr(v->path, '.');
1258
1259 if (d1 && d2) {
1260 int r;
1261
1262 r = strcasecmp(d1, d2);
1263 if (r != 0)
1264 return r;
1265 }
1266
1267 return strcasecmp(basename(u->path), basename(v->path));
1268}
1269
1270static bool_Bool output_show_unit_file(const UnitFileList *u, char **patterns) {
1271 if (!strv_fnmatch_or_empty(patterns, basename(u->path), FNM_NOESCAPE(1 << 1)))
1272 return false0;
1273
1274 if (!strv_isempty(arg_types)) {
1275 const char *dot;
1276
1277 dot = strrchr(u->path, '.');
1278 if (!dot)
1279 return false0;
1280
1281 if (!strv_find(arg_types, dot+1))
1282 return false0;
1283 }
1284
1285 if (!strv_isempty(arg_states) &&
1286 !strv_find(arg_states, unit_file_state_to_string(u->state)))
1287 return false0;
1288
1289 return true1;
1290}

1453static int list_dependencies_print(const char *name, int level, unsigned int branches, bool_Bool last) {
1454 _cleanup_free___attribute__((cleanup(freep))) char *n = NULL((void*)0);
1455 size_t max_len = MAX(columns(),20u)__extension__ ({ const typeof((columns())) __unique_prefix_A512
= ((columns())); const typeof((20u)) __unique_prefix_B513 = (
(20u)); __unique_prefix_A512 > __unique_prefix_B513 ? __unique_prefix_A512
: __unique_prefix_B513; });
1456 size_t len = 0;
1457 int i;
1458
1459 if (!arg_plain) {
1460
1461 for (i = level - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
1462 len += 2;
1463 if (len > max_len - 3 && !arg_full) {
1464 printf("%s...\n",max_len % 2 ? "" : " ");
1465 return 0;
1466 }
1467 printf("%s", draw_special_char(branches & (1 << i) ? DRAW_TREE_VERTICAL : DRAW_TREE_SPACE));
1468 }
1469 len += 2;
1470
1471 if (len > max_len - 3 && !arg_full) {
1472 printf("%s...\n",max_len % 2 ? "" : " ");
1473 return 0;
1474 }
1475
1476 printf("%s", draw_special_char(last ? DRAW_TREE_RIGHT : DRAW_TREE_BRANCH));
1477 }
1478
1479 if (arg_full) {
1480 printf("%s\n", name);
1481 return 0;
1482 }
1483
1484 n = ellipsize(name, max_len-len, 100);
1485 if (!n)
1486 return log_oom()log_oom_internal("src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 1486, __func__);
1487
1488 printf("%s\n", n);
1489 return 0;
1490}

1492static int list_dependencies_get_dependencies(sd_bus *bus, const char *name, char ***deps) {
1493

1495 [DEPENDENCY_FORWARD] = "Requires\0"

1584static int list_dependencies_compare(const void *_a, const void *_b) {
1585 const char **a = (const char**) _a, **b = (const char**) _b;
1586
1587 if (unit_name_to_type(*a) == UNIT_TARGET && unit_name_to_type(*b) != UNIT_TARGET)
1588 return 1;
1589 if (unit_name_to_type(*a) != UNIT_TARGET && unit_name_to_type(*b) == UNIT_TARGET)
1590 return -1;
1591
1592 return strcasecmp(*a, *b);
1593}

1595static int list_dependencies_one(
1596 sd_bus *bus,
1597 const char *name,
1598 int level,
1599 char ***units,
1600 unsigned int branches) {
1601
1602 _cleanup_strv_free___attribute__((cleanup(strv_freep))) char **deps = NULL((void*)0);
1603 char **c;
1604 int r = 0;
1605
1606 assert(bus)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(bus)),0))) log_assert_failed(
"bus", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 1606, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
1607 assert(name)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(name)),0))) log_assert_failed
("name", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 1607, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
1608 assert(units)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(units)),0))) log_assert_failed
("units", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 1608, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
1609
1610 r = strv_extend(units, name);
1611 if (r < 0)
1612 return log_oom()log_oom_internal("src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 1612, __func__);
1613
1614 r = list_dependencies_get_dependencies(bus, name, &deps);
1615 if (r < 0)
1616 return r;
1617
1618 qsort_safe(deps, strv_length(deps), sizeof (char*), list_dependencies_compare);
1619
1620 STRV_FOREACH(c, deps)for ((c) = (deps); (c) && *(c); (c)++) {
1621 if (strv_contains(*units, *c)(!!strv_find((*units), (*c)))) {
1622 if (!arg_plain) {
1623 r = list_dependencies_print("...", level + 1, (branches << 1) | (c[1] == NULL((void*)0) ? 0 : 1), 1);
1624 if (r < 0)
1625 return r;
1626 }
1627 continue;
1628 }
1629
1630 if (arg_plain)
1631 printf(" ");
1632 else {
1633 UnitActiveState active_state = _UNIT_ACTIVE_STATE_INVALID;
1634 const char *on;
1635
1636 (void) get_state_one_unit(bus, *c, &active_state);
1637 switch (active_state) {
1638 case UNIT_ACTIVE:
1639 case UNIT_RELOADING:
1640 case UNIT_ACTIVATING:
1641 on = ansi_highlight_green();
1642 break;
1643
1644 case UNIT_INACTIVE:
1645 case UNIT_DEACTIVATING:
1646 on = ansi_normal();
1647 break;
1648
1649 default:
1650 on = ansi_highlight_red();
1651 break;
1652 }
1653
1654 printf("%s%s%s ", on, draw_special_char(DRAW_BLACK_CIRCLE), ansi_normal());
1655 }
1656
1657 r = list_dependencies_print(*c, level, branches, c[1] == NULL((void*)0));
1658 if (r < 0)
1659 return r;
1660
1661 if (arg_all || unit_name_to_type(*c) == UNIT_TARGET) {
1662 r = list_dependencies_one(bus, *c, level + 1, units, (branches << 1) | (c[1] == NULL((void*)0) ? 0 : 1));
1663 if (r < 0)
1664 return r;
1665 }
1666 }
1667
1668 if (!arg_plain)
1669 strv_remove(*units, name);
1670
1671 return 0;
1672}

1701struct machine_info {
1702 bool_Bool is_host;
1703 char *name;
1704 char *state;
1705 char *control_group;
1706 uint32_t n_failed_units;
1707 uint32_t n_jobs;
1708 usec_t timestamp;
1709};

1711static const struct bus_properties_map machine_info_property_map[] = {
1712 { "SystemState", "s", NULL((void*)0), offsetof(struct machine_info, state)__builtin_offsetof(struct machine_info, state) },
1713 { "NJobs", "u", NULL((void*)0), offsetof(struct machine_info, n_jobs)__builtin_offsetof(struct machine_info, n_jobs) },
1714 { "NFailedUnits", "u", NULL((void*)0), offsetof(struct machine_info, n_failed_units)__builtin_offsetof(struct machine_info, n_failed_units) },
1715 { "ControlGroup", "s", NULL((void*)0), offsetof(struct machine_info, control_group)__builtin_offsetof(struct machine_info, control_group) },
1716 { "UserspaceTimestamp", "t", NULL((void*)0), offsetof(struct machine_info, timestamp)__builtin_offsetof(struct machine_info, timestamp) },
1717 {}
1718};
1719
1720static void machine_info_clear(struct machine_info *info) {
1721 if (info) {
1722 free(info->name);
1723 free(info->state);
1724 free(info->control_group);
1725 zero(*info)((memset((&(*info)), 0, (sizeof(*info)))));
1726 }
1727}
1728
1729static void free_machines_list(struct machine_info *machine_infos, int n) {
1730 int i;
1731
1732 if (!machine_infos)
1733 return;
1734
1735 for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
1736 machine_info_clear(&machine_infos[i]);
1737
1738 free(machine_infos);
1739}
1740
1741static int compare_machine_info(const void *a, const void *b) {
1742 const struct machine_info *u = a, *v = b;
1743
1744 if (u->is_host != v->is_host)
1745 return u->is_host > v->is_host ? -1 : 1;
1746
1747 return strcasecmp(u->name, v->name);
1748}

1852 jobslen = MAX(jobslen, DECIMAL_STR_WIDTH(m->n_jobs))__extension__ ({ const typeof((jobslen)) __unique_prefix_A520

1911static int list_machines(int argc, char *argv[], void *userdata) {
1912 struct machine_info *machine_infos = NULL((void*)0);
1913 sd_bus *bus;
1914 int r;
1915
1916 if (geteuid() != 0) {
1917 log_error("Must be root.")({ int _level = (3), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 1917, __func__, "Must be root.") : -abs(_e); });
1918 return -EPERM1;
1919 }
1920
1921 pager_open(arg_no_pager, false0);
1922
1923 r = acquire_bus(BUS_MANAGER, &bus);
1924 if (r < 0)
1925 return r;
1926
1927 r = get_machine_list(bus, &machine_infos, strv_skip(argv, 1));
1928 if (r < 0)
1929 return r;
1930
1931 qsort_safe(machine_infos, r, sizeof(struct machine_info), compare_machine_info);
1932 output_machines_list(machine_infos, r);
1933 free_machines_list(machine_infos, r);
1934
1935 return 0;
1936}

2136static int list_jobs(int argc, char *argv[], void *userdata) {

2141 size_t size = 0;
2142 unsigned c = 0;
2143 sd_bus *bus;
2144 uint32_t id;
2145 int r;
2146 bool_Bool skipped = false0;

2149

2152 return r;

2155 bus,
2156 "org.freedesktop.systemd1",

2159 "ListJobs",
2160 &error,
2161 &reply,
2162 NULL((void*)0));

, 2164, __func__, "Failed to list jobs: %s", bus_error_message
(&error, r)) : -abs(_e); });
2165
2166 r = sd_bus_message_enter_container(reply, 'a', "(usssoo)");
2167 if (r < 0)
2168 return bus_log_parse_error(r);
2169
2170 while ((r = sd_bus_message_read(reply, "(usssoo)", &id, &name, &type, &state, &job_path, &unit_path)) > 0) {

2185

2187 if (r < 0)

2189
2190 output_jobs_list(jobs, c, skipped);
2191 return 0;

2236static int need_daemon_reload(sd_bus *bus, const char *unit) {
2237 _cleanup_(sd_bus_message_unrefp)__attribute__((cleanup(sd_bus_message_unrefp))) sd_bus_message *reply = NULL((void*)0);

2241 /* We ignore all errors here, since this is used to show a
2242 * warning only */

2245 * don't want to load the unit if it isn't loaded. */
2246
2247 r = sd_bus_call_method(
2248 bus,
2249 "org.freedesktop.systemd1",
2250 "/org/freedesktop/systemd1",
2251 "org.freedesktop.systemd1.Manager",
2252 "GetUnit",
2253 NULL((void*)0),
2254 &reply,
2255 "s", unit);
2256 if (r < 0)
2257 return r;
2258
2259 r = sd_bus_message_read(reply, "o", &path);
2260 if (r < 0)
2261 return r;
2262
2263 r = sd_bus_get_property_trivial(
2264 bus,
2265 "org.freedesktop.systemd1",
2266 path,
2267 "org.freedesktop.systemd1.Unit",
2268 "NeedDaemonReload",
2269 NULL((void*)0),
2270 'b', &b);

2272 return r;

2274 return b;
2275}

2406 if (dropin_paths && !strv_isempty(dropins)) {
2407 *dropin_paths = dropins;
2408 dropins = NULL((void*)0);
2409 r = 1;
2410 }
2411
2412 if (r == 0)
2413 log_error("No files found for %s.", unit_name)({ int _level = (3), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 2413, __func__, "No files found for %s.", unit_name) : -abs
(_e); });
2414
2415 return r;
2416}

2418static int get_state_one_unit(sd_bus *bus, const char *name, UnitActiveState *active_state) {
2419 _cleanup_(sd_bus_error_free)__attribute__((cleanup(sd_bus_error_free))) sd_bus_error error = SD_BUS_ERROR_NULL((const sd_bus_error) {(((void*)0)), (((void*)0)), 0});
2420 _cleanup_(sd_bus_message_unrefp)__attribute__((cleanup(sd_bus_message_unrefp))) sd_bus_message *reply = NULL((void*)0);
2421 _cleanup_free___attribute__((cleanup(freep))) char *buf = NULL((void*)0);
2422 UnitActiveState state;
2423 const char *path;
2424 int r;
2425
2426 assert(name)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(name)),0))) log_assert_failed
("name", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 2426, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
2427 assert(active_state)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(active_state)),0))) log_assert_failed
("active_state", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 2427, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
2428
2429 /* We don't use unit_dbus_path_from_name() directly since we don't want to load the unit unnecessarily, if it
2430 * isn't loaded. */
2431 r = sd_bus_call_method(
2432 bus,
2433 "org.freedesktop.systemd1",
2434 "/org/freedesktop/systemd1",
2435 "org.freedesktop.systemd1.Manager",
2436 "GetUnit",
2437 &error,
2438 &reply,
2439 "s", name);
2440 if (r < 0) {
2441 if (!sd_bus_error_has_name(&error, BUS_ERROR_NO_SUCH_UNIT"org.freedesktop.systemd1.NoSuchUnit"))
2442 return log_error_errno(r, "Failed to retrieve unit: %s", bus_error_message(&error, r))({ int _level = (3), _e = (r); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 2442, __func__, "Failed to retrieve unit: %s", bus_error_message
(&error, r)) : -abs(_e); });
2443
2444 /* The unit is currently not loaded, hence say it's "inactive", since all units that aren't loaded are
2445 * considered inactive. */
2446 state = UNIT_INACTIVE;
2447
2448 } else {
2449 r = sd_bus_message_read(reply, "o", &path);
2450 if (r < 0)
2451 return bus_log_parse_error(r);
2452
2453 r = sd_bus_get_property_string(
2454 bus,
2455 "org.freedesktop.systemd1",
2456 path,
2457 "org.freedesktop.systemd1.Unit",
2458 "ActiveState",
2459 &error,
2460 &buf);
2461 if (r < 0)
2462 return log_error_errno(r, "Failed to retrieve unit state: %s", bus_error_message(&error, r))({ int _level = (3), _e = (r); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 2462, __func__, "Failed to retrieve unit state: %s", bus_error_message
(&error, r)) : -abs(_e); });
2463
2464 state = unit_active_state_from_string(buf);
2465 if (state == _UNIT_ACTIVE_STATE_INVALID) {
2466 log_error("Invalid unit state '%s' for: %s", buf, name)({ int _level = (3), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 2466, __func__, "Invalid unit state '%s' for: %s", buf, name
) : -abs(_e); });
2467 return -EINVAL22;
2468 }
2469 }
2470
2471 *active_state = state;
2472 return 0;
2473}

2557static const char *verb_to_method(const char *verb) {
2558 uint i;
2559
2560 for (i = 0; i < ELEMENTSOF(unit_actions)__extension__ (__builtin_choose_expr( !__builtin_types_compatible_p
(typeof(unit_actions), typeof(&*(unit_actions))), sizeof(
unit_actions)/sizeof((unit_actions)[0]), (void)0)); i++)
2561 if (streq_ptr(unit_actions[i].verb, verb))
2562 return unit_actions[i].method;
2563
2564 return "StartUnit";
2565}

2567static const char *method_to_verb(const char *method) {

(typeof(unit_actions), typeof(&*(unit_actions))), sizeof(
unit_actions)/sizeof((unit_actions)[0]), (void)0)); i++)
2571 if (streq_ptr(unit_actions[i].method, method))
2572 return unit_actions[i].verb;

2574 return "n/a";

2621 arg_scope == UNIT_FILE_SYSTEM ? "" : " --user",({ int _level = (3), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"

== UNIT_FILE_SYSTEM ? "" : " --user", name) : -abs(_e); })
2622 name)({ int _level = (3), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 2622, __func__, "See %s logs and 'systemctl%s status %s' for details."

2644static int expand_names(sd_bus *bus, char **names, const char* suffix, char ***ret) {
2645 _cleanup_strv_free___attribute__((cleanup(strv_freep))) char **mangled = NULL((void*)0), **globs = NULL((void*)0);
2646 char **name;
2647 int r, i;
2648
2649 assert(bus)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(bus)),0))) log_assert_failed(
"bus", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 2649, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
2650 assert(ret)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(ret)),0))) log_assert_failed(
"ret", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 2650, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
2651
2652 STRV_FOREACH(name, names)for ((name) = (names); (name) && *(name); (name)++) {
2653 char *t;
2654
2655 if (suffix)
2656 r = unit_name_mangle_with_suffix(*name, UNIT_NAME_GLOB, suffix, &t);
2657 else
2658 r = unit_name_mangle(*name, UNIT_NAME_GLOB, &t);
2659 if (r < 0)
2660 return log_error_errno(r, "Failed to mangle name: %m")({ int _level = (3), _e = (r); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 2660, __func__, "Failed to mangle name: %m") : -abs(_e); });
2661
2662 if (string_is_glob(t))
2663 r = strv_consume(&globs, t);
2664 else
2665 r = strv_consume(&mangled, t);
2666 if (r < 0)
2667 return log_oom()log_oom_internal("src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 2667, __func__);
2668 }
2669
2670 /* Query the manager only if any of the names are a glob, since
2671 * this is fairly expensive */
2672 if (!strv_isempty(globs)) {
2673 _cleanup_(sd_bus_message_unrefp)__attribute__((cleanup(sd_bus_message_unrefp))) sd_bus_message *reply = NULL((void*)0);
2674 _cleanup_free___attribute__((cleanup(freep))) UnitInfo *unit_infos = NULL((void*)0);
2675 size_t allocated, n;
2676
2677 r = get_unit_list(bus, NULL((void*)0), globs, &unit_infos, 0, &reply);
2678 if (r < 0)
2679 return r;
2680
2681 n = strv_length(mangled);
2682 allocated = n + 1;
2683
2684 for (i = 0; i < r; i++) {
2685 if (!GREEDY_REALLOC(mangled, allocated, n+2)greedy_realloc((void**) &(mangled), &(allocated), (n+
2), sizeof((mangled)[0])))
2686 return log_oom()log_oom_internal("src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 2686, __func__);
2687
2688 mangled[n] = strdup(unit_infos[i].id);
2689 if (!mangled[n])
2690 return log_oom()log_oom_internal("src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 2690, __func__);
2691
2692 mangled[++n] = NULL((void*)0);
2693 }
2694 }
2695
2696 *ret = mangled;
2697 mangled = NULL((void*)0); /* do not free */
2698
2699 return 0;
2700}

2724static enum action verb_to_action(const char *verb) {
2725 enum action i;
2726
2727 for (i = _ACTION_INVALID; i < _ACTION_MAX; i++)
2728 if (streq_ptr(action_table[i].verb, verb))
2729 return i;
2730
2731 return _ACTION_INVALID;
2732}
2733
2734static int start_unit(int argc, char *argv[], void *userdata) {
2735 _cleanup_(bus_wait_for_jobs_freep)__attribute__((cleanup(bus_wait_for_jobs_freep))) BusWaitForJobs *w = NULL((void*)0);
2736 const char *method, *mode, *one_name, *suffix = NULL((void*)0);
2737 _cleanup_strv_free___attribute__((cleanup(strv_freep))) char **names = NULL((void*)0);
2738 sd_bus *bus;
2739 char **name;
2740 int r = 0;
2741
2742 ask_password_agent_open_if_enabled();
2743 polkit_agent_open_if_enabled();
2744
2745 r = acquire_bus(BUS_MANAGER, &bus);
2746 if (r < 0)
2747 return r;
2748
2749 if (arg_action == ACTION_SYSTEMCTL) {
2750 enum action action;
2751
2752 method = verb_to_method(argv[0]);
2753 action = verb_to_action(argv[0]);
2754
2755 if (streq(argv[0], "isolate")(strcmp((argv[0]),("isolate")) == 0)) {
2756 mode = "isolate";
2757 suffix = ".target";
2758 } else
2759 mode = action_table[action].mode ?: arg_job_mode;
2760
2761 one_name = action_table[action].target;
2762 } else {
2763 assert(arg_action < ELEMENTSOF(action_table))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(arg_action < __extension__
(__builtin_choose_expr( !__builtin_types_compatible_p(typeof
(action_table), typeof(&*(action_table))), sizeof(action_table
)/sizeof((action_table)[0]), (void)0)))),0))) log_assert_failed
("arg_action < ELEMENTSOF(action_table)", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 2763, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); } while (0);
2764 assert(action_table[arg_action].target)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(action_table[arg_action].target
)),0))) log_assert_failed("action_table[arg_action].target", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 2764, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); } while (0);
2765
2766 method = "StartUnit";
2767
2768 mode = action_table[arg_action].mode;
2769 one_name = action_table[arg_action].target;
2770 }
2771
2772 if (one_name)
2773 names = strv_new(one_name, NULL((void*)0));
2774 else {
2775 r = expand_names(bus, strv_skip(argv, 1), suffix, &names);
2776 if (r < 0)
2777 return log_error_errno(r, "Failed to expand names: %m")({ int _level = (3), _e = (r); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 2777, __func__, "Failed to expand names: %m") : -abs(_e); }
);
2778 }
2779
2780 if (!arg_no_block) {
2781 r = bus_wait_for_jobs_new(bus, &w);
2782 if (r < 0)
2783 return log_error_errno(r, "Could not watch jobs: %m")({ int _level = (3), _e = (r); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 2783, __func__, "Could not watch jobs: %m") : -abs(_e); });
2784 }
2785
2786 STRV_FOREACH(name, names)for ((name) = (names); (name) && *(name); (name)++) {
2787 _cleanup_(sd_bus_error_free)__attribute__((cleanup(sd_bus_error_free))) sd_bus_error error = SD_BUS_ERROR_NULL((const sd_bus_error) {(((void*)0)), (((void*)0)), 0});
2788 int q;
2789
2790 q = start_unit_one(bus, method, *name, mode, &error, w);
2791 if (r >= 0 && q < 0)
2792 r = translate_bus_error_to_exit_status(q, &error);
2793 }
2794
2795 if (!arg_no_block) {
2796 int q, arg_count = 0;
2797 const char* extra_args[4] = {};
2798
2799 if (arg_scope != UNIT_FILE_SYSTEM)
2800 extra_args[arg_count++] = "--user";
2801
2802 assert(IN_SET(arg_transport, BUS_TRANSPORT_LOCAL, BUS_TRANSPORT_REMOTE, BUS_TRANSPORT_MACHINE))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(({ _Bool _found = 0; static __attribute__
((unused)) char _static_assert__macros_need_to_be_extended[20
- sizeof((int[]){BUS_TRANSPORT_LOCAL, BUS_TRANSPORT_REMOTE, BUS_TRANSPORT_MACHINE
})/sizeof(int)]; switch(arg_transport) { case BUS_TRANSPORT_LOCAL
: case BUS_TRANSPORT_REMOTE: case BUS_TRANSPORT_MACHINE: _found
= 1; break; default: break; } _found; }))),0))) log_assert_failed
("IN_SET(arg_transport, BUS_TRANSPORT_LOCAL, BUS_TRANSPORT_REMOTE, BUS_TRANSPORT_MACHINE)"
, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 2802, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); } while
(0);
2803 if (arg_transport == BUS_TRANSPORT_REMOTE) {
2804 extra_args[arg_count++] = "-H";
2805 extra_args[arg_count++] = arg_host;
2806 } else if (arg_transport == BUS_TRANSPORT_MACHINE) {
2807 extra_args[arg_count++] = "-M";
2808 extra_args[arg_count++] = arg_host;
2809 }
2810
2811 q = bus_wait_for_jobs(w, arg_quiet, extra_args);
2812 if (q < 0)
2813 return q;
2814
2815 /* When stopping units, warn if they can still be triggered by
2816 * another active unit (socket, path, timer) */
2817 if (!arg_quiet && streq(method, "StopUnit")(strcmp((method),("StopUnit")) == 0))
2818 STRV_FOREACH(name, names)for ((name) = (names); (name) && *(name); (name)++)
2819 check_triggering_units(bus, *name);
2820 }
2821
2822 return r;
2823}

2894 description = "hibernate system";
2895 break;

2912 &error,
2913 NULL((void*)0),

) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"

bus_error_message(&error, r)) : -abs(_e); });

) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 3024, __func__, "User %s is logged in on %s.", strna(user),

) : -abs(_e); });

3026 }
3027

3030
3031 log_error("Please retry operation after closing inhibitors and logging out other users.\nAlternatively, ignore inhibitors and users with 'systemctl %s -i'.",({ int _level = (3), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 3032, __func__, "Please retry operation after closing inhibitors and logging out other users.\nAlternatively, ignore inhibitors and users with 'systemctl %s -i'."
, action_table[a].verb) : -abs(_e); })
3032 action_table[a].verb)({ int _level = (3), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"

3035#else

3305static int exec_status_info_deserialize(sd_bus_message *m, ExecStatusInfo *i) {
3306 uint64_t start_timestamp, exit_timestamp, start_timestamp_monotonic, exit_timestamp_monotonic;
3307 const char *path;
3308 uint32_t pid;
3309 int32_t code, status;
3310 int ignore, r;
3311
3312 assert(m)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(m)),0))) log_assert_failed("m"
, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 3312, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); } while
(0);
3313 assert(i)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(i)),0))) log_assert_failed("i"
, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 3313, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); } while
(0);
3314
3315 r = sd_bus_message_enter_container(m, SD_BUS_TYPE_STRUCT, "sasbttttuii");
3316 if (r < 0)
3317 return bus_log_parse_error(r);
3318 else if (r == 0)
3319 return 0;
3320
3321 r = sd_bus_message_read(m, "s", &path);
3322 if (r < 0)
3323 return bus_log_parse_error(r);
3324
3325 i->path = strdup(path);
3326 if (!i->path)
3327 return log_oom()log_oom_internal("src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 3327, __func__);
3328
3329 r = sd_bus_message_read_strv(m, &i->argv);
3330 if (r < 0)
3331 return bus_log_parse_error(r);
3332
3333 r = sd_bus_message_read(m,
3334 "bttttuii",
3335 &ignore,
3336 &start_timestamp, &start_timestamp_monotonic,
3337 &exit_timestamp, &exit_timestamp_monotonic,
3338 &pid,
3339 &code, &status);
3340 if (r < 0)
3341 return bus_log_parse_error(r);
3342
3343 i->ignore = ignore;
3344 i->start_timestamp = (usec_t) start_timestamp;
3345 i->exit_timestamp = (usec_t) exit_timestamp;
3346 i->pid = (pid_t) pid;
3347 i->code = code;
3348 i->status = status;
3349
3350 r = sd_bus_message_exit_container(m);
3351 if (r < 0)
3352 return bus_log_parse_error(r);
3353
3354 return 1;
3355}

3611

3613 if (p->code == 0)
3614 continue;
3615
3616 argv = strv_join(p->argv, " ");
3617 printf(" Process: "PID_FMT"%" "i"" %s=%s ", p->pid, p->name, strna(argv));
3618
3619 good = is_clean_exit_lsb(p->code, p->status, NULL((void*)0));
3620 if (!good) {
3621 on = ansi_highlight_red();
3622 off = ansi_normal();
3623 } else
3624 on = off = "";
3625
3626 printf("%s(code=%s, ", on, sigchld_code_to_string(p->code));
3627
3628 if (p->code == CLD_EXITEDCLD_EXITED) {
3629 const char *c;
3630
3631 printf("status=%i", p->status);
3632
3633 c = exit_status_to_string(p->status, EXIT_STATUS_SYSTEMD);
3634 if (c)
3635 printf("/%s", c);
3636
3637 } else
3638 printf("signal=%s", signal_to_string(p->status));
3639
3640 printf(")%s\n", off);
3641
3642 if (i->main_pid == p->pid &&
3643 i->start_timestamp == p->start_timestamp &&
3644 i->exit_timestamp == p->start_timestamp)
3645 /* Let's not show this twice */
3646 i->main_pid = 0;
3647
3648 if (p->pid == i->control_pid)
3649 i->control_pid = 0;
3650 }
3651
3652 if (i->main_pid > 0 || i->control_pid > 0) {
3653 if (i->main_pid > 0) {
3654 printf(" Main PID: "PID_FMT"%" "i", i->main_pid);
3655
3656 if (i->running) {
3657 _cleanup_free___attribute__((cleanup(freep))) char *comm = NULL((void*)0);
3658 get_process_comm(i->main_pid, &comm);
3659 if (comm)
3660 printf(" (%s)", comm);
3661 } else if (i->exit_code > 0) {
3662 printf(" (code=%s, ", sigchld_code_to_string(i->exit_code));
3663
3664 if (i->exit_code == CLD_EXITEDCLD_EXITED) {
3665 const char *c;
3666
3667 printf("status=%i", i->exit_status);
3668
3669 c = exit_status_to_string(i->exit_status, EXIT_STATUS_SYSTEMD);
3670 if (c)
3671 printf("/%s", c);
3672
3673 } else
3674 printf("signal=%s", signal_to_string(i->exit_status));
3675 printf(")");
3676 }
3677
3678 if (i->control_pid > 0)
3679 printf(";");
3680 }
3681
3682 if (i->control_pid > 0) {
3683 _cleanup_free___attribute__((cleanup(freep))) char *c = NULL((void*)0);
3684
3685 printf(" %8s: "PID_FMT"%" "i", i->main_pid ? "" : " Control", i->control_pid);
3686
3687 get_process_comm(i->control_pid, &c);
3688 if (c)
3689 printf(" (%s)", c);
3690 }
3691
3692 printf("\n");
3693 }
3694
3695 if (i->status_text)
3696 printf(" Status: \"%s\"\n", i->status_text);
3697 if (i->status_errno > 0)
3698 printf(" Error: %i (%s)\n", i->status_errno, strerror(i->status_errno));
3699
3700 if (i->tasks_current != (uint64_t) -1) {
3701 printf(" Tasks: %" PRIu64"l" "u", i->tasks_current);
3702
3703 if (i->tasks_max != (uint64_t) -1)
3704 printf(" (limit: %" PRIi64"l" "i" ")\n", i->tasks_max);
3705 else
3706 printf("\n");
3707 }
3708
3709 if (i->memory_current != (uint64_t) -1) {
3710 char buf[FORMAT_BYTES_MAX8];
3711
3712 printf(" Memory: %s", format_bytes(buf, sizeof(buf), i->memory_current));
3713
3714 if (i->memory_limit != (uint64_t) -1)
3715 printf(" (limit: %s)\n", format_bytes(buf, sizeof(buf), i->memory_limit));
3716 else
3717 printf("\n");
3718 }
3719
3720 if (i->cpu_usage_nsec != (uint64_t) -1) {
3721 char buf[FORMAT_TIMESPAN_MAX64];
3722 printf(" CPU: %s\n", format_timespan(buf, sizeof(buf), i->cpu_usage_nsec / NSEC_PER_USEC((nsec_t) 1000ULL), USEC_PER_MSEC((usec_t) 1000ULL)));
3723 }
3724
3725 if (i->control_group &&
3726 (i->main_pid > 0 || i->control_pid > 0 ||
3727 (!IN_SET(arg_transport, BUS_TRANSPORT_LOCAL, BUS_TRANSPORT_MACHINE)({ _Bool _found = 0; static __attribute__ ((unused)) char _static_assert__macros_need_to_be_extended
[20 - sizeof((int[]){BUS_TRANSPORT_LOCAL, BUS_TRANSPORT_MACHINE
})/sizeof(int)]; switch(arg_transport) { case BUS_TRANSPORT_LOCAL
: case BUS_TRANSPORT_MACHINE: _found = 1; break; default: break
; } _found; }) || cg_is_empty_recursive(SYSTEMD_CGROUP_CONTROLLER"name=systemd", i->control_group) == 0))) {
3728 unsigned c;
3729
3730 printf(" CGroup: %s\n", i->control_group);
3731
3732 if (IN_SET(arg_transport,({ _Bool _found = 0; static __attribute__ ((unused)) char _static_assert__macros_need_to_be_extended
[20 - sizeof((int[]){BUS_TRANSPORT_LOCAL, BUS_TRANSPORT_MACHINE
})/sizeof(int)]; switch(arg_transport) { case BUS_TRANSPORT_LOCAL
: case BUS_TRANSPORT_MACHINE: _found = 1; break; default: break
; } _found; })
3733 BUS_TRANSPORT_LOCAL,({ _Bool _found = 0; static __attribute__ ((unused)) char _static_assert__macros_need_to_be_extended
[20 - sizeof((int[]){BUS_TRANSPORT_LOCAL, BUS_TRANSPORT_MACHINE
})/sizeof(int)]; switch(arg_transport) { case BUS_TRANSPORT_LOCAL
: case BUS_TRANSPORT_MACHINE: _found = 1; break; default: break
; } _found; })
3734 BUS_TRANSPORT_MACHINE)({ _Bool _found = 0; static __attribute__ ((unused)) char _static_assert__macros_need_to_be_extended
[20 - sizeof((int[]){BUS_TRANSPORT_LOCAL, BUS_TRANSPORT_MACHINE
})/sizeof(int)]; switch(arg_transport) { case BUS_TRANSPORT_LOCAL
: case BUS_TRANSPORT_MACHINE: _found = 1; break; default: break
; } _found; })) {
3735 unsigned k = 0;
3736 pid_t extra[2];
3737 static const char prefix[] = " ";
3738
3739 c = columns();
3740 if (c > sizeof(prefix) - 1)
3741 c -= sizeof(prefix) - 1;
3742 else
3743 c = 0;
3744
3745 if (i->main_pid > 0)
3746 extra[k++] = i->main_pid;
3747
3748 if (i->control_pid > 0)
3749 extra[k++] = i->control_pid;
3750
3751 show_cgroup_and_extra(SYSTEMD_CGROUP_CONTROLLER"name=systemd", i->control_group, prefix, c, false0, extra, k, get_output_flags());
3752 }
3753 }
3754
3755 if (i->id && arg_transport == BUS_TRANSPORT_LOCAL)
3756 show_journal_by_unit(
3757 stdoutstdout,
3758 i->id,
3759 arg_output,
3760 0,
3761 i->inactive_exit_timestamp_monotonic,
3762 arg_lines,
3763 getuid(),
3764 get_output_flags() | OUTPUT_BEGIN_NEWLINE,
3765 SD_JOURNAL_LOCAL_ONLY,
3766 arg_scope == UNIT_FILE_SYSTEM,
3767 ellipsized);
3768
3769 if (i->need_daemon_reload)
3770 warn_unit_file_changed(i->id);
3771}

4114static int print_property(const char *name, sd_bus_message *m, const char *contents) {
4115 int r;
4116
4117 assert(name)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(name)),0))) log_assert_failed

); } while (0);
4118 assert(m)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(m)),0))) log_assert_failed("m"

4120 /* This is a low-level property printer, see
4121 * print_status_info() for the nicer output */
4122
4123 if (arg_properties && !strv_find(arg_properties, name)) {
4124 /* skip what we didn't read */

4412static int show_one(

4419
4420 _cleanup_(sd_bus_message_unrefp)__attribute__((cleanup(sd_bus_message_unrefp))) sd_bus_message *reply = NULL((void*)0);

4447 return log_error_errno(r, "Failed to get properties: %s", bus_error_message(&error, r))({ int _level = (3), _e = (r); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"

4459 const char *name, *contents;
4460
4461 r = sd_bus_message_read(reply, "s", &name);
4462 if (r < 0)
4463 return bus_log_parse_error(r);
4464

4466 if (r < 0)

4477 if (r < 0)
4478 return r;
4479

4481 if (r < 0)
4482 return bus_log_parse_error(r);
4483
4484 r = sd_bus_message_exit_container(reply);
4485 if (r < 0)
4486 return bus_log_parse_error(r);
4487 }
4488 if (r < 0)
4489 return bus_log_parse_error(r);
4490
4491 r = sd_bus_message_exit_container(reply);
4492 if (r < 0)
4493 return bus_log_parse_error(r);

4495 r = 0;

4499 show_unit_help(&info);
4500 else

4509 !streq_ptr(info.active_state, "reloading") &&
4510 streq(verb, "status")(strcmp((verb),("status")) == 0)) {
4511 /* According to LSB: "program not running" */
4512 /* 0: program is running or service is OK
4513 * 1: program is dead and /run PID file exists
4514 * 2: program is dead and /run/lock lock file exists
4515 * 3: program is not running
4516 * 4: program or service status is unknown
4517 */
4518 if (info.pid_file && access(info.pid_file, F_OK0) == 0)
4519 r = 1;
4520 else
4521 r = 3;
4522 }

("*_head == _item", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 4525, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0); *_head = _item->exec_next; } _item->exec_next
= _item->exec_prev = ((void*)0); } while (0);
4526 exec_status_info_free(p);
4527 }
4528
4529 return r;
4530}

4566static int show_all(
4567 const char* verb,
4568 sd_bus *bus,
4569 bool_Bool show_properties,
4570 bool_Bool *new_line,
4571 bool_Bool *ellipsized) {
4572
4573 _cleanup_(sd_bus_message_unrefp)__attribute__((cleanup(sd_bus_message_unrefp))) sd_bus_message *reply = NULL((void*)0);
4574 _cleanup_free___attribute__((cleanup(freep))) UnitInfo *unit_infos = NULL((void*)0);
4575 const UnitInfo *u;
4576 unsigned c;
4577 int r, ret = 0;
4578
4579 r = get_unit_list(bus, NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0), &unit_infos, 0, &reply);
4580 if (r < 0)
4581 return r;
4582
4583 pager_open(arg_no_pager, false0);
4584
4585 c = (unsigned) r;
4586
4587 qsort_safe(unit_infos, c, sizeof(UnitInfo), compare_unit_info);
4588
4589 for (u = unit_infos; u < unit_infos + c; u++) {
4590 _cleanup_free___attribute__((cleanup(freep))) char *p = NULL((void*)0);
4591
4592 p = unit_dbus_path_from_name(u->id);
4593 if (!p)
4594 return log_oom()log_oom_internal("src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 4594, __func__);
4595
4596 r = show_one(verb, bus, p, show_properties, new_line, ellipsized);
4597 if (r < 0)
4598 return r;
4599 else if (r > 0 && ret == 0)
4600 ret = r;
4601 }
4602
4603 return ret;
4604}

4606static int show_system_status(sd_bus *bus) {
4607 char since1[FORMAT_TIMESTAMP_RELATIVE_MAX256], since2[FORMAT_TIMESTAMP_MAX((4*4+1)+11+9+4+1)];
4608 _cleanup_free___attribute__((cleanup(freep))) char *hn = NULL((void*)0);
4609 _cleanup_(machine_info_clear)__attribute__((cleanup(machine_info_clear))) struct machine_info mi = {};

4611 int r;
4612
4613 hn = gethostname_malloc();
4614 if (!hn)

4616
4617 r = bus_map_all_properties(bus, "org.freedesktop.systemd1", "/org/freedesktop/systemd1", machine_info_property_map, &mi);

4619 return log_error_errno(r, "Failed to read server status: %m")({ int _level = (3), _e = (r); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"

_e); });
4620
4621 if (streq_ptr(mi.state, "degraded")) {
4622 on = ansi_highlight_red();

4625 on = ansi_highlight_yellow();
4626 off = ansi_normal();

4629

4631
4632 printf(" State: %s%s%s\n",
4633 on, strna(mi.state), off);
4634

4637
4638 printf(" Since: %s; %s\n",
4639 format_timestamp(since2, sizeof(since2), mi.timestamp),
4640 format_timestamp_relative(since1, sizeof(since1), mi.timestamp));

4642 printf(" CGroup: %s\n", mi.control_group ?: "/");
4643 if (IN_SET(arg_transport,({ _Bool _found = 0; static __attribute__ ((unused)) char _static_assert__macros_need_to_be_extended
[20 - sizeof((int[]){BUS_TRANSPORT_LOCAL, BUS_TRANSPORT_MACHINE
})/sizeof(int)]; switch(arg_transport) { case BUS_TRANSPORT_LOCAL

4924static int daemon_reload(int argc, char *argv[], void *userdata) {
4925 _cleanup_(sd_bus_error_free)__attribute__((cleanup(sd_bus_error_free))) sd_bus_error error = SD_BUS_ERROR_NULL((const sd_bus_error) {(((void*)0)), (((void*)0)), 0});
4926 const char *method;
4927 sd_bus *bus;
4928 int r;
4929
4930 polkit_agent_open_if_enabled();
4931
4932 r = acquire_bus(BUS_MANAGER, &bus);
4933 if (r < 0)
4934 return r;
4935
4936 if (arg_action == ACTION_RELOAD)
4937 method = "Reload";
4938 else if (arg_action == ACTION_REEXEC)
4939 method = "Reexecute";
4940 else {
4941 assert(arg_action == ACTION_SYSTEMCTL)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(arg_action == ACTION_SYSTEMCTL
)),0))) log_assert_failed("arg_action == ACTION_SYSTEMCTL", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 4941, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); } while (0);
4942
4943 method =
4944 streq(argv[0], "clear-jobs")(strcmp((argv[0]),("clear-jobs")) == 0) ||
4945 streq(argv[0], "cancel")(strcmp((argv[0]),("cancel")) == 0) ? "ClearJobs" :
4946 streq(argv[0], "daemon-reexec")(strcmp((argv[0]),("daemon-reexec")) == 0) ? "Reexecute" :
4947 streq(argv[0], "reset-failed")(strcmp((argv[0]),("reset-failed")) == 0) ? "ResetFailed" :
4948 streq(argv[0], "halt")(strcmp((argv[0]),("halt")) == 0) ? "Halt" :
4949 streq(argv[0], "poweroff")(strcmp((argv[0]),("poweroff")) == 0) ? "PowerOff" :
4950 streq(argv[0], "reboot")(strcmp((argv[0]),("reboot")) == 0) ? "Reboot" :
4951 streq(argv[0], "kexec")(strcmp((argv[0]),("kexec")) == 0) ? "KExec" :
4952 streq(argv[0], "exit")(strcmp((argv[0]),("exit")) == 0) ? "Exit" :
4953 /* "daemon-reload" */ "Reload";
4954 }
4955
4956 r = sd_bus_call_method(
4957 bus,
4958 "org.freedesktop.systemd1",
4959 "/org/freedesktop/systemd1",
4960 "org.freedesktop.systemd1.Manager",
4961 method,
4962 &error,
4963 NULL((void*)0),
4964 NULL((void*)0));
4965 if (r == -ENOENT2 && arg_action != ACTION_SYSTEMCTL)
4966 /* There's always a fallback possible for
4967 * legacy actions. */
4968 r = -EADDRNOTAVAIL99;
4969 else if ((r == -ETIMEDOUT110 || r == -ECONNRESET104) && streq(method, "Reexecute")(strcmp((method),("Reexecute")) == 0))
4970 /* On reexecution, we expect a disconnect, not a
4971 * reply */
4972 r = 0;
4973 else if (r < 0)
4974 return log_error_errno(r, "Failed to execute operation: %s", bus_error_message(&error, r))({ int _level = (3), _e = (r); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 4974, __func__, "Failed to execute operation: %s", bus_error_message
(&error, r)) : -abs(_e); });
4975
4976 return r < 0 ? r : 0;
4977}

5169static int import_environment(int argc, char *argv[], void *userdata) {
5170 _cleanup_(sd_bus_error_free)__attribute__((cleanup(sd_bus_error_free))) sd_bus_error error = SD_BUS_ERROR_NULL((const sd_bus_error) {(((void*)0)), (((void*)0)), 0});
5171 _cleanup_(sd_bus_message_unrefp)__attribute__((cleanup(sd_bus_message_unrefp))) sd_bus_message *m = NULL((void*)0);

5175 polkit_agent_open_if_enabled();

5179 return r;

5181 r = sd_bus_message_new_method_call(
5182 bus,
5183 &m,
5184 "org.freedesktop.systemd1",
5185 "/org/freedesktop/systemd1",

5189 return bus_log_create_error(r);

5198 return bus_log_create_error(r);

5201

) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"

5204 return -EINVAL22;
5205 }
5206
5207 STRV_FOREACH(b, environ)for ((b) = (environ); (b) && *(b); (b)++) {
5208 const char *eq;
5209
5210 eq = startswith(*b, *a);
5211 if (eq && *eq == '=') {
5212
5213 r = sd_bus_message_append(m, "s", *b);
5214 if (r < 0)
5215 return bus_log_create_error(r);
5216
5217 break;
5218 }
5219 }
5220 }
5221
5222 r = sd_bus_message_close_container(m);

5224 if (r < 0)

5411static int enable_unit(int argc, char *argv[], void *userdata) {

5414 UnitFileChange *changes = NULL((void*)0);
5415 unsigned n_changes = 0;

5417 int r;
5418
5419 if (!argv[1])
5420 return 0;
5421

5429
5430 /* If the operation was fully executed by the SysV compat,
5431 * let's finish early */
5432 if (strv_isempty(names))
5433 return 0;
5434
5435 if (install_client_side()) {
5436 if (streq(verb, "enable")(strcmp((verb),("enable")) == 0)) {

5439 } else if (streq(verb, "disable")(strcmp((verb),("disable")) == 0))

5441 else if (streq(verb, "reenable")(strcmp((verb),("reenable")) == 0)) {
5442 r = unit_file_reenable(arg_scope, arg_runtime, arg_root, names, arg_force, &changes, &n_changes);
5443 carries_install_info = r;
5444 } else if (streq(verb, "link")(strcmp((verb),("link")) == 0))
5445 r = unit_file_link(arg_scope, arg_runtime, arg_root, names, arg_force, &changes, &n_changes);
5446 else if (streq(verb, "preset")(strcmp((verb),("preset")) == 0)) {
5447 r = unit_file_preset(arg_scope, arg_runtime, arg_root, names, arg_preset_mode, arg_force, &changes, &n_changes);
5448 carries_install_info = r;
5449 } else if (streq(verb, "mask")(strcmp((verb),("mask")) == 0))
5450 r = unit_file_mask(arg_scope, arg_runtime, arg_root, names, arg_force, &changes, &n_changes);
5451 else if (streq(verb, "unmask")(strcmp((verb),("unmask")) == 0))

, 5454, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); } while (0);
5455
5456 if (r == -ESHUTDOWN108)
5457 return log_error_errno(r, "Unit file is masked.")({ int _level = (3), _e = (r); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 5457, __func__, "Unit file is masked.") : -abs(_e); });
5458 if (r < 0)
5459 return log_error_errno(r, "Operation failed: %m")({ int _level = (3), _e = (r); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 5459, __func__, "Operation failed: %m") : -abs(_e); });
5460
5461 if (!arg_quiet)
5462 dump_unit_file_changes(changes, n_changes);
5463
5464 r = 0;
5465 } else {
5466 _cleanup_(sd_bus_message_unrefp)__attribute__((cleanup(sd_bus_message_unrefp))) sd_bus_message *reply = NULL((void*)0), *m = NULL((void*)0);
5467 _cleanup_(sd_bus_error_free)__attribute__((cleanup(sd_bus_error_free))) sd_bus_error error = SD_BUS_ERROR_NULL((const sd_bus_error) {(((void*)0)), (((void*)0)), 0});
5468 int expect_carries_install_info = false0;
5469 bool_Bool send_force = true1, send_preset_mode = false0;

5472

5474

5476 if (r < 0)
5477 return r;

5480 method = "EnableUnitFiles";

5482 } else if (streq(verb, "disable")(strcmp((verb),("disable")) == 0)) {
5483 method = "DisableUnitFiles";

5809 }
5810
5811 return !enabled;
5812}

5814static int is_system_running(int argc, char *argv[], void *userdata) {
5815 _cleanup_free___attribute__((cleanup(freep))) char *state = NULL((void*)0);
5816 sd_bus *bus;
5817 int r;
5818
5819 if (running_in_chroot() > 0 || (arg_transport == BUS_TRANSPORT_LOCAL && !sd_booted())) {
5820 if (!arg_quiet)
5821 puts("offline");
5822 return EXIT_FAILURE1;
5823 }
5824
5825 r = acquire_bus(BUS_MANAGER, &bus);
5826 if (r < 0)
5827 return r;
5828
5829 r = sd_bus_get_property_string(
5830 bus,
5831 "org.freedesktop.systemd1",
5832 "/org/freedesktop/systemd1",
5833 "org.freedesktop.systemd1.Manager",
5834 "SystemState",
5835 NULL((void*)0),
5836 &state);
5837 if (r < 0) {
5838 if (!arg_quiet)
5839 puts("unknown");
5840 return 0;
5841 }
5842
5843 if (!arg_quiet)
5844 puts(state);
5845
5846 return streq(state, "running")(strcmp((state),("running")) == 0) ? EXIT_SUCCESS0 : EXIT_FAILURE1;
5847}

5849static int create_edit_temp_file(const char *new_path, const char *original_path, char **ret_tmp_fn) {

5881static int get_file_to_edit(const char *name, const char *user_home, const char *user_runtime, char **ret_path) {
5882 _cleanup_free___attribute__((cleanup(freep))) char *path = NULL((void*)0), *path2 = NULL((void*)0), *run = NULL((void*)0);
5883
5884 assert(name)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(name)),0))) log_assert_failed
("name", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 5884, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
5885 assert(ret_path)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(ret_path)),0))) log_assert_failed
("ret_path", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 5885, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
5886
5887 switch (arg_scope) {
5888 case UNIT_FILE_SYSTEM:
5889 path = path_join(arg_root, SYSTEM_CONFIG_UNIT_PATH"/usr/etc/systemd/system", name);
5890 if (arg_runtime)
5891 run = path_join(arg_root, "/run/systemd/system/", name);
5892 break;
5893 case UNIT_FILE_GLOBAL:
5894 path = path_join(arg_root, USER_CONFIG_UNIT_PATH"/usr/etc/systemd/user", name);
5895 if (arg_runtime)
5896 run = path_join(arg_root, "/run/systemd/user/", name);
5897 break;
5898 case UNIT_FILE_USER:
5899 assert(user_home)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(user_home)),0))) log_assert_failed
("user_home", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 5899, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
5900 assert(user_runtime)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(user_runtime)),0))) log_assert_failed
("user_runtime", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 5900, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
5901
5902 path = path_join(arg_root, user_home, name);
5903 if (arg_runtime) {
5904 path2 = path_join(arg_root, USER_CONFIG_UNIT_PATH"/usr/etc/systemd/user", name);
5905 if (!path2)
5906 return log_oom()log_oom_internal("src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 5906, __func__);
5907 run = path_join(arg_root, user_runtime, name);
5908 }
5909 break;
5910 default:
5911 assert_not_reached("Invalid scope")do { log_assert_failed_unreachable("Invalid scope", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 5911, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); } while (0);
5912 }
5913 if (!path || (arg_runtime && !run))
5914 return log_oom()log_oom_internal("src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 5914, __func__);
5915
5916 if (arg_runtime) {
5917 if (access(path, F_OK0) >= 0) {
5918 log_error("Refusing to create \"%s\" because it would be overridden by \"%s\" anyway.", run, path)({ int _level = (3), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 5918, __func__, "Refusing to create \"%s\" because it would be overridden by \"%s\" anyway."
, run, path) : -abs(_e); });
5919 return -EEXIST17;
5920 }
5921
5922 if (path2 && access(path2, F_OK0) >= 0) {
5923 log_error("Refusing to create \"%s\" because it would be overridden by \"%s\" anyway.", run, path2)({ int _level = (3), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 5923, __func__, "Refusing to create \"%s\" because it would be overridden by \"%s\" anyway."
, run, path2) : -abs(_e); });
5924 return -EEXIST17;
5925 }
5926
5927 *ret_path = run;
5928 run = NULL((void*)0);
5929 } else {
5930 *ret_path = path;
5931 path = NULL((void*)0);
5932 }
5933
5934 return 0;
5935}

5962static int unit_file_create_copy(
5963 const char *unit_name,
5964 const char *fragment_path,
5965 const char *user_home,
5966 const char *user_runtime,
5967 char **ret_new_path,
5968 char **ret_tmp_path) {
5969
5970 char *tmp_new_path, *tmp_tmp_path;
5971 int r;
5972
5973 assert(fragment_path)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(fragment_path)),0))) log_assert_failed
("fragment_path", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 5973, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
5974 assert(unit_name)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(unit_name)),0))) log_assert_failed

); } while (0);
5975 assert(ret_new_path)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(ret_new_path)),0))) log_assert_failed
("ret_new_path", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 5975, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
5976 assert(ret_tmp_path)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(ret_tmp_path)),0))) log_assert_failed
("ret_tmp_path", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 5976, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
5977
5978 r = get_file_to_edit(unit_name, user_home, user_runtime, &tmp_new_path);
5979 if (r < 0)
5980 return r;
5981
5982 if (!path_equal(fragment_path, tmp_new_path) && access(tmp_new_path, F_OK0) == 0) {
5983 char response;
5984
5985 r = ask_char(&response, "yn", "\"%s\" already exists. Overwrite with \"%s\"? [(y)es, (n)o] ", tmp_new_path, fragment_path);
5986 if (r < 0) {
5987 free(tmp_new_path);
5988 return r;
5989 }
5990 if (response != 'y') {

) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 5991, __func__, "%s ignored", unit_name) : -abs(_e); });
5992 free(tmp_new_path);
5993 return -1;
5994 }
5995 }
5996
5997 r = create_edit_temp_file(tmp_new_path, fragment_path, &tmp_tmp_path);
5998 if (r < 0) {
5999 log_error_errno(r, "Failed to create temporary file for \"%s\": %m", tmp_new_path)({ int _level = (3), _e = (r); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 5999, __func__, "Failed to create temporary file for \"%s\": %m"
, tmp_new_path) : -abs(_e); });
6000 free(tmp_new_path);
6001 return r;
6002 }
6003
6004 *ret_new_path = tmp_new_path;
6005 *ret_tmp_path = tmp_tmp_path;
6006
6007 return 0;
6008}

6010static int run_editor(char **paths) {
6011 pid_t pid;
6012 int r;
6013
6014 assert(paths)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(paths)),0))) log_assert_failed
("paths", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 6014, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
6015
6016 pid = fork();
6017 if (pid < 0)
6018 return log_error_errno(errno, "Failed to fork: %m")({ int _level = (3), _e = ((*__errno_location ())); (log_get_max_level
() >= ((_level) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 6018, __func__, "Failed to fork: %m") : -abs(_e); });
6019
6020 if (pid == 0) {
6021 const char **args;
6022 char *editor, **editor_args = NULL((void*)0);
6023 char **tmp_path, **original_path, *p;
6024 unsigned n_editor_args = 0, i = 1;
6025 size_t argc;
6026
6027 (void) reset_all_signal_handlers();
6028 (void) reset_signal_mask();
6029
6030 argc = strv_length(paths)/2 + 1;
6031
6032 /* SYSTEMD_EDITOR takes precedence over EDITOR which takes precedence over VISUAL
6033 * If neither SYSTEMD_EDITOR nor EDITOR nor VISUAL are present,
6034 * we try to execute well known editors
6035 */
6036 editor = getenv("SYSTEMD_EDITOR");
6037 if (!editor)
6038 editor = getenv("EDITOR");
6039 if (!editor)
6040 editor = getenv("VISUAL");
6041
6042 if (!isempty(editor)) {
6043 editor_args = strv_split(editor, WHITESPACE" \t\n\r");
6044 if (!editor_args) {
6045 (void) log_oom()log_oom_internal("src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 6045, __func__);
6046 _exit(EXIT_FAILURE1);
6047 }
6048 n_editor_args = strv_length(editor_args);
6049 argc += n_editor_args - 1;
6050 }
6051 args = newa(const char*, argc + 1)((const char**) __builtin_alloca (sizeof(const char*)*(argc +
1)));
6052
6053 if (n_editor_args > 0) {
6054 args[0] = editor_args[0];
6055 for (; i < n_editor_args; i++)
6056 args[i] = editor_args[i];
6057 }
6058
6059 STRV_FOREACH_PAIR(original_path, tmp_path, paths)for ((original_path) = (paths), (tmp_path) = (original_path+1
); (original_path) && *(original_path) && *(tmp_path
); (original_path) += 2, (tmp_path) = (original_path + 1)) {
6060 args[i] = *tmp_path;
6061 i++;
6062 }
6063 args[i] = NULL((void*)0);
6064
6065 if (n_editor_args > 0)
6066 execvp(args[0], (char* const*) args);
6067
6068 FOREACH_STRING(p, "editor", "nano", "vim", "vi")for (char **_l = ({ char **_ll = ((char**) ((const char*[]) {
"editor", "nano", "vim", "vi", ((void*)0) })); p = _ll ? _ll
[0] : ((void*)0); _ll; }); _l && *_l; p = ({ _l ++; _l
[0]; })) {
6069 args[0] = p;
6070 execvp(p, (char* const*) args);
6071 /* We do not fail if the editor doesn't exist
6072 * because we want to try each one of them before
6073 * failing.
6074 */
6075 if (errno(*__errno_location ()) != ENOENT2) {
6076 log_error_errno(errno, "Failed to execute %s: %m", editor)({ int _level = (3), _e = ((*__errno_location ())); (log_get_max_level
() >= ((_level) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 6076, __func__, "Failed to execute %s: %m", editor) : -abs(
_e); });
6077 _exit(EXIT_FAILURE1);
6078 }
6079 }
6080
6081 log_error("Cannot edit unit(s), no editor available. Please set either $SYSTEMD_EDITOR, $EDITOR or $VISUAL.")({ int _level = (3), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 6081, __func__, "Cannot edit unit(s), no editor available. Please set either $SYSTEMD_EDITOR, $EDITOR or $VISUAL."
) : -abs(_e); });
6082 _exit(EXIT_FAILURE1);
6083 }
6084
6085 r = wait_for_terminate_and_warn("editor", pid, true1);
6086 if (r < 0)
6087 return log_error_errno(r, "Failed to wait for child: %m")({ int _level = (3), _e = (r); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 6087, __func__, "Failed to wait for child: %m") : -abs(_e);
});
6088
6089 return 0;
6090}

6092static int find_paths_to_edit(sd_bus *bus, char **names, char ***paths) {
6093 _cleanup_free___attribute__((cleanup(freep))) char *user_home = NULL((void*)0);
6094 _cleanup_free___attribute__((cleanup(freep))) char *user_runtime = NULL((void*)0);
6095 _cleanup_lookup_paths_free___attribute__((cleanup(lookup_paths_free))) LookupPaths lp = {};
6096 char **name;
6097 int r;
6098
6099 assert(names)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(names)),0))) log_assert_failed
("names", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 6099, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
6100 assert(paths)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(paths)),0))) log_assert_failed
("paths", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 6100, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
6101
6102 r = init_home_and_lookup_paths(&user_home, &user_runtime, &lp);
6103 if (r < 0)
6104 return r;
6105
6106 STRV_FOREACH(name, names)for ((name) = (names); (name) && *(name); (name)++) {
6107 _cleanup_free___attribute__((cleanup(freep))) char *path = NULL((void*)0);
6108 char *new_path, *tmp_path;
6109
6110 r = unit_find_paths(bus, *name, &lp, &path, NULL((void*)0));
6111 if (r < 0)
6112 return r;
6113 else if (r == 0)
6114 return -ENOENT2;
6115 else if (!path) {
6116 // FIXME: support units with path==NULL (no FragmentPath)
6117 log_error("No fragment exists for %s.", *name)({ int _level = (3), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 6117, __func__, "No fragment exists for %s.", *name) : -abs
(_e); });
6118 return -ENOENT2;
6119 }
6120
6121 if (arg_full)
6122 r = unit_file_create_copy(*name, path, user_home, user_runtime, &new_path, &tmp_path);
6123 else
6124 r = unit_file_create_dropin(*name, user_home, user_runtime, &new_path, &tmp_path);
6125 if (r < 0)
6126 return r;
6127
6128 r = strv_push_pair(paths, new_path, tmp_path);
6129 if (r < 0)
6130 return log_oom()log_oom_internal("src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 6130, __func__);
6131 }
6132
6133 return 0;
6134}
6135
6136static int edit(int argc, char *argv[], void *userdata) {
6137 _cleanup_strv_free___attribute__((cleanup(strv_freep))) char **names = NULL((void*)0);
6138 _cleanup_strv_free___attribute__((cleanup(strv_freep))) char **paths = NULL((void*)0);
6139 char **original, **tmp;
6140 sd_bus *bus;
6141 int r;
6142
6143 if (!on_tty()) {
6144 log_error("Cannot edit units if not on a tty.")({ int _level = (3), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 6144, __func__, "Cannot edit units if not on a tty.") : -abs
(_e); });
6145 return -EINVAL22;
6146 }
6147
6148 if (arg_transport != BUS_TRANSPORT_LOCAL) {
6149 log_error("Cannot edit units remotely.")({ int _level = (3), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 6149, __func__, "Cannot edit units remotely.") : -abs(_e); }
);
6150 return -EINVAL22;
6151 }
6152
6153 r = acquire_bus(BUS_MANAGER, &bus);
6154 if (r < 0)
6155 return r;
6156
6157 r = expand_names(bus, strv_skip(argv, 1), NULL((void*)0), &names);
6158 if (r < 0)
6159 return log_error_errno(r, "Failed to expand names: %m")({ int _level = (3), _e = (r); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 6159, __func__, "Failed to expand names: %m") : -abs(_e); }
);
6160
6161 r = find_paths_to_edit(bus, names, &paths);
6162 if (r < 0)
6163 return r;
6164
6165 if (strv_isempty(paths))
6166 return -ENOENT2;
6167
6168 r = run_editor(paths);
6169 if (r < 0)
6170 goto end;
6171
6172 STRV_FOREACH_PAIR(original, tmp, paths)for ((original) = (paths), (tmp) = (original+1); (original) &&
*(original) && *(tmp); (original) += 2, (tmp) = (original
+ 1)) {
6173 /* If the temporary file is empty we ignore it. It's
6174 * useful if the user wants to cancel its modification
6175 */
6176 if (null_or_empty_path(*tmp)) {
6177 log_warning("Editing \"%s\" canceled: temporary file is empty.", *original)({ int _level = (4), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 6177, __func__, "Editing \"%s\" canceled: temporary file is empty."
, *original) : -abs(_e); });
6178 continue;
6179 }
6180
6181 r = rename(*tmp, *original);
6182 if (r < 0) {
6183 r = log_error_errno(errno, "Failed to rename \"%s\" to \"%s\": %m", *tmp, *original)({ int _level = (3), _e = ((*__errno_location ())); (log_get_max_level
() >= ((_level) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 6183, __func__, "Failed to rename \"%s\" to \"%s\": %m", *tmp
, *original) : -abs(_e); });
6184 goto end;
6185 }
6186 }
6187
6188 r = 0;
6189
6190 if (!arg_no_reload && !install_client_side())
6191 r = daemon_reload(argc, argv, userdata);
6192
6193end:
6194 STRV_FOREACH_PAIR(original, tmp, paths)for ((original) = (paths), (tmp) = (original+1); (original) &&
*(original) && *(tmp); (original) += 2, (tmp) = (original
+ 1)) {
6195 (void) unlink(*tmp);
6196
6197 /* Removing empty dropin dirs */
6198 if (!arg_full) {
6199 _cleanup_free___attribute__((cleanup(freep))) char *dir;
6200
6201 dir = dirname_malloc(*original);
6202 if (!dir)
6203 return log_oom()log_oom_internal("src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 6203, __func__);
6204
6205 /* no need to check if the dir is empty, rmdir
6206 * does nothing if it is not the case.
6207 */
6208 (void) rmdir(dir);
6209 }
6210 }
6211
6212 return r;
6213}

6356 program_invocation_short_name,
6357 arg_action == ACTION_REBOOT ? " [ARG]" : "",
6358 arg_action == ACTION_REBOOT ? "Reboot" :
6359 arg_action == ACTION_POWEROFF ? "Power off" :
6360 "Halt");
