6481
6482static int systemctl_parse_argv(int argc, char *argv[]) {
6483
6484 enum {
6485 ARG_FAIL = 0x100,
6486 ARG_REVERSE,
6487 ARG_AFTER,
6488 ARG_BEFORE,
6489 ARG_SHOW_TYPES,
6490 ARG_IRREVERSIBLE,
6491 ARG_IGNORE_DEPENDENCIES,
6492 ARG_VERSION,
6493 ARG_USER,
6494 ARG_SYSTEM,
6495 ARG_GLOBAL,
6496 ARG_NO_BLOCK,
6497 ARG_NO_LEGEND,
6498 ARG_NO_PAGER,
6499 ARG_NO_WALL,
6500 ARG_ROOT,
6501 ARG_NO_RELOAD,
6502 ARG_KILL_WHO,
6503 ARG_NO_ASK_PASSWORD,
6504 ARG_FAILED,
6505 ARG_RUNTIME,
6506 ARG_FORCE,
6507 ARG_PLAIN,
6508 ARG_STATE,
6509 ARG_JOB_MODE,
6510 ARG_PRESET_MODE,
6511 ARG_FIRMWARE_SETUP,
6512 ARG_NOW,
6513 ARG_MESSAGE,
6514 };
6515
6516 static const struct option options[] = {
6517 { "help", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), 'h' },
6518 { "version", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_VERSION },
6519 { "type", required_argument1, NULL((void*)0), 't' },
6520 { "property", required_argument1, NULL((void*)0), 'p' },
6521 { "all", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), 'a' },
6522 { "reverse", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_REVERSE },
6523 { "after", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_AFTER },
6524 { "before", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_BEFORE },
6525 { "show-types", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_SHOW_TYPES },
6526 { "failed", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_FAILED }, /* compatibility only */
6527 { "full", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), 'l' },
6528 { "job-mode", required_argument1, NULL((void*)0), ARG_JOB_MODE },
6529 { "fail", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_FAIL }, /* compatibility only */
6530 { "irreversible", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_IRREVERSIBLE }, /* compatibility only */
6531 { "ignore-dependencies", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_IGNORE_DEPENDENCIES }, /* compatibility only */
6532 { "ignore-inhibitors", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), 'i' },
6533 { "user", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_USER },
6534 { "system", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_SYSTEM },
6535 { "global", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_GLOBAL },
6536 { "no-block", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_NO_BLOCK },
6537 { "no-legend", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_NO_LEGEND },
6538 { "no-pager", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_NO_PAGER },
6539 { "no-wall", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_NO_WALL },
6540 { "quiet", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), 'q' },
6541 { "root", required_argument1, NULL((void*)0), ARG_ROOT },
6542 { "force", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_FORCE },
6543 { "no-reload", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_NO_RELOAD },
6544 { "kill-who", required_argument1, NULL((void*)0), ARG_KILL_WHO },
6545 { "signal", required_argument1, NULL((void*)0), 's' },
6546 { "no-ask-password", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_NO_ASK_PASSWORD },
6547 { "host", required_argument1, NULL((void*)0), 'H' },
6548 { "machine", required_argument1, NULL((void*)0), 'M' },
6549 { "runtime", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_RUNTIME },
6550 { "lines", required_argument1, NULL((void*)0), 'n' },
6551 { "output", required_argument1, NULL((void*)0), 'o' },
6552 { "plain", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_PLAIN },
6553 { "state", required_argument1, NULL((void*)0), ARG_STATE },
6554 { "recursive", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), 'r' },
6555 { "preset-mode", required_argument1, NULL((void*)0), ARG_PRESET_MODE },
6556 { "firmware-setup", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_FIRMWARE_SETUP },
6557 { "now", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_NOW },
6558 { "message", required_argument1, NULL((void*)0), ARG_MESSAGE },
6559 {}
6560 };
6561
6562 const char *p;
6563 int c, r;
6564
6565 assert(argc >= 0)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(argc >= 0)),0))) log_assert_failed
("argc >= 0", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 6565, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
6566 assert(argv)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(argv)),0))) log_assert_failed
("argv", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 6566, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
6567
6568 /* we default to allowing interactive authorization only in systemctl (not in the legacy commands) */
6569 arg_ask_password = true1;
6570
6571 while ((c = getopt_long(argc, argv, "ht:p:alqfs:H:M:n:o:ir", options, NULL((void*)0))) >= 0)
6572
6573 switch (c) {
6574
6575 case 'h':
6576 systemctl_help();
6577 return 0;
6578
6579 case ARG_VERSION:
6580 return version();
6581
6582 case 't': {
6583 if (isempty(optarg)) {
6584 log_error("--type requires arguments.")({ int _level = (3), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 6584, __func__, "--type requires arguments.") : -abs(_e); }
);
6585 return -EINVAL22;
6586 }
6587
6588 p = optarg;
6589 for (;;) {
6590 _cleanup_free___attribute__((cleanup(freep))) char *type = NULL((void*)0);
6591
6592 r = extract_first_word(&p, &type, ",", 0);
6593 if (r < 0)
6594 return log_error_errno(r, "Failed to parse type: %s", optarg)({ int _level = (3), _e = (r); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 6594, __func__, "Failed to parse type: %s", optarg) : -abs(
_e); });
6595
6596 if (r == 0)
6597 break;
6598
6599 if (streq(type, "help")(strcmp((type),("help")) == 0)) {
6600 help_types();
6601 return 0;
6602 }
6603
6604 if (unit_type_from_string(type) >= 0) {
6605 if (strv_push(&arg_types, type) < 0)
6606 return log_oom()log_oom_internal("src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 6606, __func__);
6607 type = NULL((void*)0);
6608 continue;
6609 }
6610
6611 /* It's much nicer to use --state= for
6612 * load states, but let's support this
6613 * in --types= too for compatibility
6614 * with old versions */
6615 if (unit_load_state_from_string(type) >= 0) {
6616 if (strv_push(&arg_states, type) < 0)
6617 return log_oom()log_oom_internal("src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 6617, __func__);
6618 type = NULL((void*)0);
6619 continue;
6620 }
6621
6622 log_error("Unknown unit type or load state '%s'.", type)({ int _level = (3), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 6622, __func__, "Unknown unit type or load state '%s'.", type
) : -abs(_e); });
6623 log_info("Use -t help to see a list of allowed values.")({ int _level = (6), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 6623, __func__, "Use -t help to see a list of allowed values."
) : -abs(_e); });
6624 return -EINVAL22;
6625 }
6626
6627 break;
6628 }
6629
6630 case 'p': {
6631 /* Make sure that if the empty property list
6632 was specified, we won't show any properties. */
6633 if (isempty(optarg) && !arg_properties) {
6634 arg_properties = new0(char*, 1)((char**) calloc((1), sizeof(char*)));
6635 if (!arg_properties)
6636 return log_oom()log_oom_internal("src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 6636, __func__);
6637 } else {
6638 p = optarg;
6639 for (;;) {
6640 _cleanup_free___attribute__((cleanup(freep))) char *prop = NULL((void*)0);
6641
6642 r = extract_first_word(&p, &prop, ",", 0);
6643 if (r < 0)
6644 return log_error_errno(r, "Failed to parse property: %s", optarg)({ int _level = (3), _e = (r); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 6644, __func__, "Failed to parse property: %s", optarg) : -
abs(_e); });
6645
6646 if (r == 0)
6647 break;
6648
6649 if (strv_push(&arg_properties, prop) < 0)
6650 return log_oom()log_oom_internal("src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 6650, __func__);
6651
6652 prop = NULL((void*)0);
6653 }
6654 }
6655
6656 /* If the user asked for a particular
6657 * property, show it to him, even if it is
6658 * empty. */
6659 arg_all = true1;
6660
6661 break;
6662 }
6663
6664 case 'a':
6665 arg_all = true1;
6666 break;
6667
6668 case ARG_REVERSE:
6669 arg_dependency = DEPENDENCY_REVERSE;
6670 break;
6671
6672 case ARG_AFTER:
6673 arg_dependency = DEPENDENCY_AFTER;
6674 break;
6675
6676 case ARG_BEFORE:
6677 arg_dependency = DEPENDENCY_BEFORE;
6678 break;
6679
6680 case ARG_SHOW_TYPES:
6681 arg_show_types = true1;
6682 break;
6683
6684 case ARG_JOB_MODE:
6685 arg_job_mode = optarg;
6686 break;
6687
6688 case ARG_FAIL:
6689 arg_job_mode = "fail";
6690 break;
6691
6692 case ARG_IRREVERSIBLE:
6693 arg_job_mode = "replace-irreversibly";
6694 break;
6695
6696 case ARG_IGNORE_DEPENDENCIES:
6697 arg_job_mode = "ignore-dependencies";
6698 break;
6699
6700 case ARG_USER:
6701 arg_scope = UNIT_FILE_USER;
6702 break;
6703
6704 case ARG_SYSTEM:
6705 arg_scope = UNIT_FILE_SYSTEM;
6706 break;
6707
6708 case ARG_GLOBAL:
6709 arg_scope = UNIT_FILE_GLOBAL;
6710 break;
6711
6712 case ARG_NO_BLOCK:
6713 arg_no_block = true1;
6714 break;
6715
6716 case ARG_NO_LEGEND:
6717 arg_no_legend = true1;
6718 break;
6719
6720 case ARG_NO_PAGER:
6721 arg_no_pager = true1;
6722 break;
6723
6724 case ARG_NO_WALL:
6725 arg_no_wall = true1;
6726 break;
6727
6728 case ARG_ROOT:

6754 break;

6811 break;

6815 break;

6890static int halt_parse_argv(int argc, char *argv[]) {
6891
6892 enum {
6893 ARG_HELP = 0x100,
6894 ARG_HALT,
6895 ARG_REBOOT,
6896 ARG_NO_WALL
6897 };
6898
6899 static const struct option options[] = {
6900 { "help", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_HELP },
6901 { "halt", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_HALT },
6902 { "poweroff", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), 'p' },
6903 { "reboot", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_REBOOT },
6904 { "force", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), 'f' },
6905 { "wtmp-only", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), 'w' },
6906 { "no-wtmp", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), 'd' },
6907 { "no-wall", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_NO_WALL },
6908 {}
6909 };
6910
6911 int c, r, runlevel;
6912
6913 assert(argc >= 0)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(argc >= 0)),0))) log_assert_failed

); } while (0);
6914 assert(argv)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(argv)),0))) log_assert_failed
("argv", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 6914, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
6915
6916 if (utmp_get_runlevel(&runlevel, NULL((void*)0)) >= 0)
6917 if (runlevel == '0' || runlevel == '6')
6918 arg_force = 2;

6920 while ((c = getopt_long(argc, argv, "pfwdnih", options, NULL((void*)0))) >= 0)
6921 switch (c) {

6934 break;
6935
6936 case ARG_REBOOT:
6937 arg_action = ACTION_REBOOT;
6938 break;
6939
6940 case 'f':

6942 break;
6943
6944 case 'w':

6946 break;
6947
6948 case 'd':
6949 arg_no_wtmp = true1;
6950 break;
6951
6952 case ARG_NO_WALL:
6953 arg_no_wall = true1;
6954 break;
6955
6956 case 'i':
6957 case 'h':
6958 case 'n':
6959 /* Compatibility nops */
6960 break;
6961
6962 case '?':
6963 return -EINVAL22;
6964
6965 default:
6966 assert_not_reached("Unhandled option")do { log_assert_failed_unreachable("Unhandled option", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 6966, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); } while (0);
6967 }

6969 if (arg_action == ACTION_REBOOT && (argc == optind || argc == optind + 1)) {
6970 r = update_reboot_param_file(argc == optind + 1 ? argv[optind] : NULL((void*)0));
6971 if (r < 0)
6972 return r;
6973 } else if (optind < argc) {
6974 log_error("Too many arguments.")({ int _level = (3), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level

6981static int parse_shutdown_time_spec(const char *t, usec_t *_u) {
6982 assert(t)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(t)),0))) log_assert_failed("t"
, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 6982, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); } while
(0);
6983 assert(_u)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(_u)),0))) log_assert_failed("_u"
, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 6983, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); } while
(0);
6984
6985 if (streq(t, "now")(strcmp((t),("now")) == 0))
6986 *_u = 0;
6987 else if (!strchr(t, ':')) {
6988 uint64_t u;
6989
6990 if (safe_atou64(t, &u) < 0)
6991 return -EINVAL22;
6992
6993 *_u = now(CLOCK_REALTIME0) + USEC_PER_MINUTE((usec_t) (60ULL*((usec_t) 1000000ULL))) * u;
6994 } else {
6995 char *e = NULL((void*)0);
6996 long hour, minute;
6997 struct tm tm = {};
6998 time_t s;
6999 usec_t n;
7000
7001 errno(*__errno_location ()) = 0;
7002 hour = strtol(t, &e, 10);
7003 if (errno(*__errno_location ()) > 0 || *e != ':' || hour < 0 || hour > 23)
7004 return -EINVAL22;
7005
7006 minute = strtol(e+1, &e, 10);
7007 if (errno(*__errno_location ()) > 0 || *e != 0 || minute < 0 || minute > 59)
7008 return -EINVAL22;
7009
7010 n = now(CLOCK_REALTIME0);
7011 s = (time_t) (n / USEC_PER_SEC((usec_t) 1000000ULL));
7012
7013 assert_se(localtime_r(&s, &tm))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(localtime_r(&s, &tm))
),0))) log_assert_failed("localtime_r(&s, &tm)", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 7013, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); } while (0);
7014
7015 tm.tm_hour = (int) hour;
7016 tm.tm_min = (int) minute;
7017 tm.tm_sec = 0;
7018
7019 assert_se(s = mktime(&tm))do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(s = mktime(&tm))),0))) log_assert_failed
("s = mktime(&tm)", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 7019, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
7020
7021 *_u = (usec_t) s * USEC_PER_SEC((usec_t) 1000000ULL);
7022
7023 while (*_u <= n)
7024 *_u += USEC_PER_DAY((usec_t) (24ULL*((usec_t) (60ULL*((usec_t) (60ULL*((usec_t) 1000000ULL
)))))));
7025 }
7026
7027 return 0;
7028}

7030static int shutdown_parse_argv(int argc, char *argv[]) {
7031
7032 enum {
7033 ARG_HELP = 0x100,
7034 ARG_NO_WALL
7035 };
7036
7037 static const struct option options[] = {
7038 { "help", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_HELP },
7039 { "halt", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), 'H' },
7040 { "poweroff", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), 'P' },
7041 { "reboot", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), 'r' },
7042 { "kexec", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), 'K' }, /* not documented extension */
7043 { "no-wall", no_argument0, NULL((void*)0), ARG_NO_WALL },
7044 {}
7045 };
7046
7047 char **wall = NULL((void*)0);
7048 int c, r;
7049
7050 assert(argc >= 0)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(argc >= 0)),0))) log_assert_failed
("argc >= 0", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 7050, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
7051 assert(argv)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(argv)),0))) log_assert_failed
("argv", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 7051, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
7052
7053 while ((c = getopt_long(argc, argv, "HPrhkKtafFc", options, NULL((void*)0))) >= 0)
7054 switch (c) {
7055
7056 case ARG_HELP:
7057 shutdown_help();
7058 return 0;
7059
7060 case 'H':
7061 arg_action = ACTION_HALT;
7062 break;
7063
7064 case 'P':
7065 arg_action = ACTION_POWEROFF;
7066 break;
7067
7068 case 'r':
7069 if (kexec_loaded())
7070 arg_action = ACTION_KEXEC;
7071 else
7072 arg_action = ACTION_REBOOT;
7073 break;
7074
7075 case 'K':
7076 arg_action = ACTION_KEXEC;
7077 break;
7078
7079 case 'h':
7080 if (arg_action != ACTION_HALT)
7081 arg_action = ACTION_POWEROFF;
7082 break;
7083
7084 case 'k':
7085 arg_dry = true1;
7086 break;
7087
7088 case ARG_NO_WALL:
7089 arg_no_wall = true1;
7090 break;
7091
7092 case 't':
7093 case 'a':
7094 case 'f':
7095 case 'F':
7096 /* Compatibility nops */
7097 break;
7098
7099 case 'c':
7100 arg_action = ACTION_CANCEL_SHUTDOWN;
7101 break;
7102
7103 case '?':
7104 return -EINVAL22;
7105
7106 default:
7107 assert_not_reached("Unhandled option")do { log_assert_failed_unreachable("Unhandled option", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 7107, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); } while (0);
7108 }
7109
7110 if (argc > optind && arg_action != ACTION_CANCEL_SHUTDOWN) {
7111 r = parse_shutdown_time_spec(argv[optind], &arg_when);
7112 if (r < 0) {
7113 log_error("Failed to parse time specification: %s", argv[optind])({ int _level = (3), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 7113, __func__, "Failed to parse time specification: %s", argv
[optind]) : -abs(_e); });
7114 return r;
7115 }
7116 } else
7117 arg_when = now(CLOCK_REALTIME0) + USEC_PER_MINUTE((usec_t) (60ULL*((usec_t) 1000000ULL)));
7118
7119 if (argc > optind && arg_action == ACTION_CANCEL_SHUTDOWN)
7120 /* No time argument for shutdown cancel */
7121 wall = argv + optind;
7122 else if (argc > optind + 1)
7123 /* We skip the time argument */
7124 wall = argv + optind + 1;
7125
7126 if (wall) {
7127 arg_wall = strv_copy(wall);
7128 if (!arg_wall)
7129 return log_oom()log_oom_internal("src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 7129, __func__);
7130 }
7131
7132 optind = argc;
7133
7134 return 1;
7135}

7261
7262static int parse_argv(int argc, char *argv[]) {
7263 assert(argc >= 0)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(argc >= 0)),0))) log_assert_failed
("argc >= 0", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 7263, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
7264 assert(argv)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(argv)),0))) log_assert_failed
("argv", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 7264, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
7265
7266 if (program_invocation_short_name) {
7267
7268 if (strstr(program_invocation_short_name, "halt")) {
7269 arg_action = ACTION_HALT;
7270 return halt_parse_argv(argc, argv);
7271 } else if (strstr(program_invocation_short_name, "poweroff")) {
7272 arg_action = ACTION_POWEROFF;
7273 return halt_parse_argv(argc, argv);
7274 } else if (strstr(program_invocation_short_name, "reboot")) {
7275 if (kexec_loaded())
7276 arg_action = ACTION_KEXEC;
7277 else
7278 arg_action = ACTION_REBOOT;
7279 return halt_parse_argv(argc, argv);
7280 } else if (strstr(program_invocation_short_name, "shutdown")) {
7281 arg_action = ACTION_POWEROFF;
7282 return shutdown_parse_argv(argc, argv);
7283 } else if (strstr(program_invocation_short_name, "init")) {
7284
7285 if (sd_booted() > 0) {
7286 arg_action = _ACTION_INVALID;
7287 return telinit_parse_argv(argc, argv);
7288 } else {
7289 /* Hmm, so some other init system is
7290 * running, we need to forward this
7291 * request to it. For now we simply
7292 * guess that it is Upstart. */
7293
7294 execv(TELINIT"/lib/sysvinit/telinit", argv);
7295
7296 log_error("Couldn't find an alternative telinit implementation to spawn.")({ int _level = (3), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 7296, __func__, "Couldn't find an alternative telinit implementation to spawn."
) : -abs(_e); });
7297 return -EIO5;
7298 }
7299
7300 } else if (strstr(program_invocation_short_name, "runlevel")) {
7301 arg_action = ACTION_RUNLEVEL;
7302 return runlevel_parse_argv(argc, argv);
7303 }
7304 }
7305
7306 arg_action = ACTION_SYSTEMCTL;
7307 return systemctl_parse_argv(argc, argv);
7308}
7309
7310#ifdef HAVE_SYSV_COMPAT
7311_pure___attribute__ ((pure)) static int action_to_runlevel(void) {
7312
7313 static const char table[_ACTION_MAX] = {
7314 [ACTION_HALT] = '0',
7315 [ACTION_POWEROFF] = '0',
7316 [ACTION_REBOOT] = '6',
7317 [ACTION_RUNLEVEL2] = '2',
7318 [ACTION_RUNLEVEL3] = '3',
7319 [ACTION_RUNLEVEL4] = '4',
7320 [ACTION_RUNLEVEL5] = '5',
7321 [ACTION_RESCUE] = '1'
7322 };
7323
7324 assert(arg_action < _ACTION_MAX)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(arg_action < _ACTION_MAX))
,0))) log_assert_failed("arg_action < _ACTION_MAX", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 7324, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); } while (0);
7325
7326 return table[arg_action];
7327}
7328#endif
7329
7330static int talk_initctl(void) {
7331#ifdef HAVE_SYSV_COMPAT
7332 struct init_request request = {
7333 .magic = INIT_MAGIC0x03091969,
7334 .sleeptime = 0,
7335 .cmd = INIT_CMD_RUNLVL1
7336 };
7337
7338 _cleanup_close___attribute__((cleanup(closep))) int fd = -1;
7339 char rl;
7340 int r;
7341
7342 rl = action_to_runlevel();
7343 if (!rl)
7344 return 0;
7345
7346 request.runlevel = rl;
7347
7348 fd = open(INIT_FIFO"/dev/initctl", O_WRONLY01|O_NDELAY04000|O_CLOEXEC02000000|O_NOCTTY0400);
7349 if (fd < 0) {
7350 if (errno(*__errno_location ()) == ENOENT2)
7351 return 0;
7352
7353 return log_error_errno(errno, "Failed to open "INIT_FIFO": %m")({ int _level = (3), _e = ((*__errno_location ())); (log_get_max_level
() >= ((_level) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 7353, __func__, "Failed to open ""/dev/initctl"": %m") : -abs
(_e); });
7354 }
7355
7356 r = loop_write(fd, &request, sizeof(request), false0);
7357 if (r < 0)
7358 return log_error_errno(r, "Failed to write to "INIT_FIFO": %m")({ int _level = (3), _e = (r); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 7358, __func__, "Failed to write to ""/dev/initctl"": %m") :
-abs(_e); });
7359
7360 return 1;
7361#else
7362 return 0;
7363#endif
7364}

7440static int reload_with_fallback(void) {
7441
7442 /* First, try systemd via D-Bus. */
7443 if (daemon_reload(0, NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0)) >= 0)
7444 return 0;
7445
7446 /* Nothing else worked, so let's try signals */
7447 assert(arg_action == ACTION_RELOAD || arg_action == ACTION_REEXEC)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(arg_action == ACTION_RELOAD ||
arg_action == ACTION_REEXEC)),0))) log_assert_failed("arg_action == ACTION_RELOAD || arg_action == ACTION_REEXEC"
, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 7447, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); } while
(0);
7448
7449 if (kill(1, arg_action == ACTION_RELOAD ? SIGHUP1 : SIGTERM15) < 0)
7450 return log_error_errno(errno, "kill() failed: %m")({ int _level = (3), _e = ((*__errno_location ())); (log_get_max_level
() >= ((_level) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 7450, __func__, "kill() failed: %m") : -abs(_e); });
7451
7452 return 0;
7453}
7454
7455static int start_with_fallback(void) {
7456
7457 /* First, try systemd via D-Bus. */
7458 if (start_unit(0, NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0)) >= 0)
7459 return 0;
7460
7461 /* Nothing else worked, so let's try
7462 * /dev/initctl */
7463 if (talk_initctl() > 0)
7464 return 0;
7465
7466 log_error("Failed to talk to init daemon.")({ int _level = (3), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 7466, __func__, "Failed to talk to init daemon.") : -abs(_e
); });
7467 return -EIO5;
7468}

7470static int halt_now(enum action a) {
7471
7472 /* The kernel will automaticall flush ATA disks and suchlike
7473 * on reboot(), but the file systems need to be synce'd
7474 * explicitly in advance. */
7475 (void) sync();
7476
7477 /* Make sure C-A-D is handled by the kernel from this point
7478 * on... */
7479 (void) reboot(RB_ENABLE_CAD0x89abcdef);
7480
7481 switch (a) {
7482
7483 case ACTION_HALT:
7484 log_info("Halting.")({ int _level = (6), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 7484, __func__, "Halting.") : -abs(_e); });
7485 (void) reboot(RB_HALT_SYSTEM0xcdef0123);
7486 return -errno(*__errno_location ());
7487
7488 case ACTION_POWEROFF:
7489 log_info("Powering off.")({ int _level = (6), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 7489, __func__, "Powering off.") : -abs(_e); });
7490 (void) reboot(RB_POWER_OFF0x4321fedc);
7491 return -errno(*__errno_location ());
7492
7493 case ACTION_KEXEC:
7494 case ACTION_REBOOT: {
7495 _cleanup_free___attribute__((cleanup(freep))) char *param = NULL((void*)0);
7496
7497 if (read_one_line_file(REBOOT_PARAM_FILE"/run/systemd/reboot-param", &param) >= 0) {
7498 log_info("Rebooting with argument '%s'.", param)({ int _level = (6), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 7498, __func__, "Rebooting with argument '%s'.", param) : -
abs(_e); });
7499 (void) syscall(SYS_reboot169, LINUX_REBOOT_MAGIC10xfee1dead, LINUX_REBOOT_MAGIC2672274793, LINUX_REBOOT_CMD_RESTART20xA1B2C3D4, param);
7500 }
7501
7502 log_info("Rebooting.")({ int _level = (6), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 7502, __func__, "Rebooting.") : -abs(_e); });
7503 (void) reboot(RB_AUTOBOOT0x01234567);
7504 return -errno(*__errno_location ());
7505 }
7506
7507 default:
7508 assert_not_reached("Unknown action.")do { log_assert_failed_unreachable("Unknown action.", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 7508, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); } while (0);
7509 }
7510}

7512static int logind_schedule_shutdown(void) {
7513
7514#ifdef HAVE_LOGIND1
7515 _cleanup_(sd_bus_error_free)__attribute__((cleanup(sd_bus_error_free))) sd_bus_error error = SD_BUS_ERROR_NULL((const sd_bus_error) {(((void*)0)), (((void*)0)), 0});
7516 char date[FORMAT_TIMESTAMP_MAX((4*4+1)+11+9+4+1)];
7517 const char *action;
7518 sd_bus *bus;
7519 int r;
7520
7521 (void) logind_set_wall_message();
7522
7523 r = acquire_bus(BUS_FULL, &bus);
7524 if (r < 0)
7525 return r;
7526
7527 switch (arg_action) {
7528 case ACTION_HALT:
7529 action = "halt";
7530 break;
7531 case ACTION_POWEROFF:
7532 action = "poweroff";
7533 break;
7534 case ACTION_KEXEC:
7535 action = "kexec";
7536 break;
7537 case ACTION_EXIT:
7538 action = "exit";
7539 break;
7540 case ACTION_REBOOT:
7541 default:
7542 action = "reboot";
7543 break;
7544 }
7545
7546 if (arg_dry)
7547 action = strjoina("dry-", action)({ const char *_appendees_[] = { "dry-", action }; char *_d_,
*_p_; int _len_ = 0; unsigned _i_; for (_i_ = 0; _i_ < __extension__
(__builtin_choose_expr( !__builtin_types_compatible_p(typeof
(_appendees_), typeof(&*(_appendees_))), sizeof(_appendees_
)/sizeof((_appendees_)[0]), (void)0)) && _appendees_[
_i_]; _i_++) _len_ += strlen(_appendees_[_i_]); _p_ = _d_ = __builtin_alloca
(_len_ + 1); for (_i_ = 0; _i_ < __extension__ (__builtin_choose_expr
( !__builtin_types_compatible_p(typeof(_appendees_), typeof(&
*(_appendees_))), sizeof(_appendees_)/sizeof((_appendees_)[0]
), (void)0)) && _appendees_[_i_]; _i_++) _p_ = stpcpy
(_p_, _appendees_[_i_]); *_p_ = 0; _d_; });
7548
7549 r = sd_bus_call_method(
7550 bus,
7551 "org.freedesktop.login1",
7552 "/org/freedesktop/login1",
7553 "org.freedesktop.login1.Manager",
7554 "ScheduleShutdown",
7555 &error,
7556 NULL((void*)0),
7557 "st",
7558 action,
7559 arg_when);
7560 if (r < 0)
7561 return log_warning_errno(r, "Failed to call ScheduleShutdown in logind, proceeding with immediate shutdown: %s", bus_error_message(&error, r))({ int _level = (4), _e = (r); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 7561, __func__, "Failed to call ScheduleShutdown in logind, proceeding with immediate shutdown: %s"
, bus_error_message(&error, r)) : -abs(_e); });
7562
7563 log_info("Shutdown scheduled for %s, use 'shutdown -c' to cancel.", format_timestamp(date, sizeof(date), arg_when))({ int _level = (6), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 7563, __func__, "Shutdown scheduled for %s, use 'shutdown -c' to cancel."
, format_timestamp(date, sizeof(date), arg_when)) : -abs(_e);
});
7564 return 0;
7565#else
7566 log_error("Cannot schedule shutdown without logind support, proceeding with immediate shutdown.")({ int _level = (3), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 7566, __func__, "Cannot schedule shutdown without logind support, proceeding with immediate shutdown."
) : -abs(_e); });
7567 return -ENOSYS38;
7568#endif
7569}
7570
7571static int halt_main(void) {
7572 int r;
7573
7574 r = logind_check_inhibitors(arg_action);
7575 if (r < 0)
7576 return r;
7577
7578 if (arg_when > 0)
7579 return logind_schedule_shutdown();
7580
7581 if (geteuid() != 0) {
7582 if (arg_dry || arg_force > 0) {
7583 log_error("Must be root.")({ int _level = (3), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 7583, __func__, "Must be root.") : -abs(_e); });
7584 return -EPERM1;
7585 }
7586
7587 /* Try logind if we are a normal user and no special
7588 * mode applies. Maybe PolicyKit allows us to shutdown
7589 * the machine. */
7590 if (IN_SET(arg_action, ACTION_POWEROFF, ACTION_REBOOT)({ _Bool _found = 0; static __attribute__ ((unused)) char _static_assert__macros_need_to_be_extended
[20 - sizeof((int[]){ACTION_POWEROFF, ACTION_REBOOT})/sizeof(
int)]; switch(arg_action) { case ACTION_POWEROFF: case ACTION_REBOOT
: _found = 1; break; default: break; } _found; })) {
7591 r = logind_reboot(arg_action);
7592 if (r >= 0)
7593 return r;
7594 if (IN_SET(r, -EOPNOTSUPP, -EINPROGRESS)({ _Bool _found = 0; static __attribute__ ((unused)) char _static_assert__macros_need_to_be_extended
[20 - sizeof((int[]){-95, -115})/sizeof(int)]; switch(r) { case
-95: case -115: _found = 1; break; default: break; } _found;
}))
7595 /* requested operation is not
7596 * supported on the local system or
7597 * already in progress */
7598 return r;
7599 /* on all other errors, try low-level operation */
7600 }
7601 }
7602
7603 if (!arg_dry && !arg_force)
7604 return start_with_fallback();
7605
7606 assert(geteuid() == 0)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(geteuid() == 0)),0))) log_assert_failed
("geteuid() == 0", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c", 7606, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__
); } while (0);
7607
7608 if (!arg_no_wtmp) {
7609 if (sd_booted() > 0)
7610 log_debug("Not writing utmp record, assuming that systemd-update-utmp is used.")({ int _level = (7), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 7610, __func__, "Not writing utmp record, assuming that systemd-update-utmp is used."
) : -abs(_e); });
7611 else {
7612 r = utmp_put_shutdown();
7613 if (r < 0)
7614 log_warning_errno(r, "Failed to write utmp record: %m")({ int _level = (4), _e = (r); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 7614, __func__, "Failed to write utmp record: %m") : -abs(_e
); });
7615 }
7616 }
7617
7618 if (arg_dry)
7619 return 0;
7620
7621 r = halt_now(arg_action);
7622 return log_error_errno(r, "Failed to reboot: %m")({ int _level = (3), _e = (r); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 7622, __func__, "Failed to reboot: %m") : -abs(_e); });
7623}
7624
7625static int runlevel_main(void) {
7626 int r, runlevel, previous;
7627
7628 r = utmp_get_runlevel(&runlevel, &previous);
7629 if (r < 0) {
7630 puts("unknown");
7631 return r;
7632 }
7633
7634 printf("%c %c\n",
7635 previous <= 0 ? 'N' : previous,
7636 runlevel <= 0 ? 'N' : runlevel);
7637
7638 return 0;
7639}

7641static int logind_cancel_shutdown(void) {
7642#ifdef HAVE_LOGIND1
7643 _cleanup_(sd_bus_error_free)__attribute__((cleanup(sd_bus_error_free))) sd_bus_error error = SD_BUS_ERROR_NULL((const sd_bus_error) {(((void*)0)), (((void*)0)), 0});
7644 sd_bus *bus;
7645 int r;
7646
7647 r = acquire_bus(BUS_FULL, &bus);
7648 if (r < 0)
7649 return r;
7650
7651 (void) logind_set_wall_message();
7652
7653 r = sd_bus_call_method(
7654 bus,
7655 "org.freedesktop.login1",
7656 "/org/freedesktop/login1",
7657 "org.freedesktop.login1.Manager",
7658 "CancelScheduledShutdown",
7659 &error,
7660 NULL((void*)0), NULL((void*)0));
7661 if (r < 0)
7662 return log_warning_errno(r, "Failed to talk to logind, shutdown hasn't been cancelled: %s", bus_error_message(&error, r))({ int _level = (4), _e = (r); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 7662, __func__, "Failed to talk to logind, shutdown hasn't been cancelled: %s"
, bus_error_message(&error, r)) : -abs(_e); });
7663
7664 return 0;
7665#else
7666 log_error("Not compiled with logind support, cannot cancel scheduled shutdowns.")({ int _level = (3), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 7666, __func__, "Not compiled with logind support, cannot cancel scheduled shutdowns."
) : -abs(_e); });
7667 return -ENOSYS38;
7668#endif
7669}
7670
7671int main(int argc, char*argv[]) {
7672 int r;
7673
7674 setlocale(LC_ALL6, "");
7675 log_parse_environment();
7676 log_open();
7677
7678 /* Explicitly not on_tty() to avoid setting cached value.
7679 * This becomes relevant for piping output which might be
7680 * ellipsized. */
7681 original_stdout_is_tty = isatty(STDOUT_FILENO1);
7682
7683 r = parse_argv(argc, argv);
7684 if (r <= 0)
7685 goto finish;
7686
7687 if (arg_action != ACTION_SYSTEMCTL && running_in_chroot() > 0) {
7688 log_info("Running in chroot, ignoring request.")({ int _level = (6), _e = (0); (log_get_max_level() >= ((_level
) & 0x07)) ? log_internal(_level, _e, "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 7688, __func__, "Running in chroot, ignoring request.") : -
abs(_e); });
7689 r = 0;
7690 goto finish;
7691 }
7692
7693 /* systemctl_main() will print an error message for the bus
7694 * connection, but only if it needs to */
7695
7696 switch (arg_action) {
7697
7698 case ACTION_SYSTEMCTL:
7699 r = systemctl_main(argc, argv);
7700 break;
7701
7702 case ACTION_HALT:
7703 case ACTION_POWEROFF:
7704 case ACTION_REBOOT:
7705 case ACTION_KEXEC:
7706 r = halt_main();
7707 break;
7708
7709 case ACTION_RUNLEVEL2:
7710 case ACTION_RUNLEVEL3:
7711 case ACTION_RUNLEVEL4:
7712 case ACTION_RUNLEVEL5:
7713 case ACTION_RESCUE:
7714 case ACTION_EMERGENCY:
7715 case ACTION_DEFAULT:
7716 r = start_with_fallback();
7717 break;
7718
7719 case ACTION_RELOAD:
7720 case ACTION_REEXEC:
7721 r = reload_with_fallback();
7722 break;
7723
7724 case ACTION_CANCEL_SHUTDOWN:
7725 r = logind_cancel_shutdown();
7726 break;
7727
7728 case ACTION_RUNLEVEL:
7729 r = runlevel_main();
7730 break;
7731
7732 case _ACTION_INVALID:
7733 default:
7734 assert_not_reached("Unknown action")do { log_assert_failed_unreachable("Unknown action", "src/systemctl/systemctl.c"
, 7734, __PRETTY_FUNCTION__); } while (0);
7735 }
7736
7737finish:
7738 pager_close();
7739 ask_password_agent_close();
7740 polkit_agent_close();
7741
7742 strv_free(arg_types);
7743 strv_free(arg_states);
7744 strv_free(arg_properties);
7745
7746 strv_free(arg_wall);
7747 free(arg_root);
7748
7749 release_busses();
7750
7751 /* Note that we return r here, not EXIT_SUCCESS, so that we can implement the LSB-like return codes */
7752
7753 return r < 0 ? EXIT_FAILURE1 : r;
7754}
